details:
Did you know that Gartner positioned eXcell as a Leader in its Magic Quadrant for End User Outsourcing? Come work for the leader today! The Business Intelligence (BI) Analyst identifies business intelligence, reporting, and data analysis needs. They work closely with clients and IT teams to turn data into critical information and knowledge that can be used to make sound business decisions. They provide data that is accurate, congruent, and reliable, and ensure the information is easily available to users for direct consumption or integration with other systems. Overview:

Design and document dashboards, alerts, and reports either on a regular recurring basis or as needed
Conduct analyses of functional business processes and functional business requirements, and participate in the development of business cases in the support of process changes and/or IT projects

Works on medium to complex and cross-functional IT and business intelligence solutions
May perform analysis for a wide range of requests using data in different formats and from various platforms
Researches business problems and creates models that help analyze those problems

5-7 years of related experience
Experience with business intelligence – reporting in BI dashboards, 2-3 years
Telemetry and instrumented data and log analysis, 2-3 years’ experience
Proficiency in Microsoft technology stack, 2-3 years
Degree in Computer Science or Engineering background

Job Number: 29766Senior Business Intelligence AnalystJob Description:Our client, a global non-profit, is seeking a Senior Business Intelligence Analyst to join their team. This person will be responsible for leading the design and support of enterprise-wide business intelligence applications and architecture including analyzing business needs and translating them into technology as well as process solutions. They will gather and analyze business requirements from internal customers, evaluate solution options, and develop recommendations in the form of functional specifications. Responsibilities:
Work with Finance stakeholders to understand business needs and develop business acumen. 
Develop and maintain deep business and IT domain expertise for area of responsibility. 
Gather and analyze business requirements from stakeholders and, based on findings, design functional specifications for BI front-end applications.
Optimize the performance of enterprise business intelligence tools by defining data to filter and index that add value to the user. 
Design and coordinate a curriculum for coaching and training customers in the use of business intelligence tools to enhance business decision-making capability. 
Research new technology and develop business cases to support enterprise-wide business intelligence solutions. 
Work closely with the Data Architect to design solutions in support of BI efforts. 
Maintain strong knowledge of the data warehouse and reporting data models. 
Serve as a thought leader and implementation strategist for BI systems that deliver meaningful and actionable information to key business personnel. 
Design, develop and deliver a training curriculum to ensure end user success and promote use of the BI environment across the organization.
Mentor and coach junior staff and business users on Business Intelligence and reporting and data mining methodology. 
Develop functional specifications in conjunction with technical staff including inputs, outputs, logic, and other details necessary to implement a solution. 
Identify and separate needs for revamped or new business processes separate from technology solutions, and work with internal customers to create business processes. 
Develop user acceptance test plan to validate the installed configuration and operation against detailed functional specifications, and review test results. 
Develop and maintain relationships with peers in the course of developing solutions or solving problems. 
Work projects through to completion while keeping project team members, stakeholders, vendors and ITS management informed of issues and overall status. May coordinate small projects as well. 
Manage time utilization to ensure that tasks are completed on or ahead of schedule, and that issues are escalated to project or ITS management.
Maintain awareness of technology and industry trends sufficient to provide input to selection of technology solutions as well as development of tools and methodologies. 
Troubleshoot BI tools, systems, and software.
Identify inefficiencies and gaps (data integrity, scalability, security, performance, manageability, etc.) in current BI environment and recommend solutions. 
Act as evangelist for BI benefits across the organization; promote BI usage to relevant departments. 
Education Requirements:Bachelor's degree in Finance, IT, or related field and 10 years of related experience; or an equivalent combination of education, training and experience.Desired Background/Skills:
Ability to multi-task. 
Ability to work well with others. 
Ability to listen and communicate well both verbally and in writing. 
Ability to work independently. 
Attention to detail and accuracy. 
Qualifications:
Excellent knowledge of MS Word, Outlook, PowerPoint, Excel. 
Finance background. 
Ability to obtain proper security clearances as noted by contracts.
General knowledge of or skill in software development methodologies.
General knowledge of or skills in developing system standards by applying industry knowledge to business needs by maintaining knowledge of information technology and research institute standards, which may include application, business intelligence, or database standards. 
General knowledge of or skills in participating in planning, design, or implementation activities under the direction of project leaders while completing tasks in the prescribed time and reporting status or issues to project leaders.
General knowledge of or skills in identifying and documenting business needs, rules and functions following standard ITS processes, defining scope of work and obtaining end user department sign off. 
General knowledge of or skills in the technology marketplace and direction for technologies relevant to one's areas of expertise or relevant to a specific set of project requirements. 
General knowledge or skill in researching and evaluating vendor offerings either for products of services meeting business and/or technical requirements, developing vendor selection criteria and, in conjunction with others, developing final recommendation on offerings.
Basic knowledge of or skills in planning, designing, developing and documenting functional requirements, including the end users' view of the system, underlying data structures and system interfaces, supplying sufficient specifications to develop or purchase needed software and acquire a hardware platform.
General knowledge of or skills in coordinating projects providing scope definition, risk analysis, and status updates to appropriate parties, as well as leadership to the project team. 
Strong knowledge of Cognos reporting or similar tool.

Alphanumeric is hiring a SENIOR BUSINESS INTELLIGENCE ANALYST to work in Durham, NC. 


Responsible for leading the design and support of enterprise-wide business intelligence applications and architecture including analyzing business needs and translating them into technology as well as process solutions. Gather and analyze business requirements from internal customers, evaluate solution options, and develop recommendations in the form of functional specifications. 

The ideal candidate will have a background in finance and financial systems (Oracle Financials, Costpoint, Understanding of GNA business costs),  and has moved from developing IBM Cognos reports to a subject matter expert and consultant who is strong with the business aspects of Business Intelligence and Data Warehouse.

Key Responsibilities:




Work with Finance stakeholders to understand business needs and develop business acumen. 


Troubleshoot BI tools, systems, and software--IBM Cognos, Cognos reports.

Identify inefficiencies and gaps (data integrity, scalability, security, performance, manageability, etc.) in current BI environment and recommend solutions. 
Develop and maintain deep business and IT domain expertise for area of responsibility. 
Gather and analyze business requirements from stakeholders and, based on findings, design functional specifications for BI front-end applications.
Optimize the performance of enterprise business intelligence tools by defining data to filter and index that add value to the user. 

Design and coordinate a curriculum for coaching and training customers in the use of business intelligence tools to enhance business decision-making capability.  


Research new technology and develop business cases to support enterprise-wide business intelligence solutions. 


Work closely with the Data Architect to design solutions in support of BI efforts.  


Maintain strong knowledge of the data warehouse and reporting data models. 


Serve as a thought leader and implementation strategist for BI systems that deliver meaningful and actionable information to key business personnel. 


Design, develop and deliver a training curriculum to ensure end user success and promote use of the BI environment across the organization.


Mentor and coach junior staff and business users onBusiness Intelligence and reporting and data mining methodology. 


Develop functional specifications in conjunction with technical staff including inputs, outputs, logic, and other details necessary to implement a solution. 


Identify and separate needs for revamped or new business processes separate from technology solutions, and work with internal customers to create business processes. 


Develop user acceptance test plan to validate the installed configuration and operation against detailed functional specifications, and review test results. 

Develop and maintain relationships with peers in the course of developing solutions or solving problems.  
Work projects through to completion while keeping project team members, stakeholders, vendors and ITS management informed of issues and overall status. May coordinate small projects as well. 
Manage time utilization to ensure that tasks are completed on or ahead of schedule, and that issues are escalated to project or ITS management.
Maintain awareness of technology and industry trends sufficient to provide input to selection of technology solutions as well as development of tools and methodologies. 

Act as evangelist for BI benefits across the organization; promote BI usage to relevant departments

Finance background.

Connections IT Services is now hiring a Microsoft Stack BI Analyst/Developer.  The Business Intelligence Developer/Analyst will be responsible for transforming data into actionable insight using the Microsoft SQL 2012+ stack of Business Intelligence products. This will be a dynamic role where you will be an integral member of a small team building an end-to-end business intelligence solution. This person should be very analytical with an even mix of business acumen and technical capability.
 
Position ID:  CITS0570
Location:  Irving, TX
Term:  FTE/CTH
 
Title:  Microsoft Stack BI Analyst
 
No Vendors
Sponsorship is not available
 
To stand out as a candidate for this role you have the following skillsets:
 
SQL, SSRS Report Development (experience with other vendor tools will be considered), PowerPivot, Power View, Qlik Sense, SharePoint, DAX, Data warehouse experience (IBM Netezza – Pure Data for Analytics), Data Visualization, Tableau
 
 
Description

The ideal candidate will have an innate curiosity and some analytical capability with a passion for learning. An understanding of web analytics, compliance related reporting, and lending are a plus and experience in designing, developing and maintaining business intelligence solutions is preferred.


Role and Responsibility
 
·       The BI Developer will be responsible for working with analysts, managers, and executives to understand and document business needs and working with other IT groups and the data warehouse team to understand the data sources. This will be a collaborative role that will be responsible in designing, building and deploying the BI solutions (e.g. reports) and conduct testing and troubleshooting.
 
·       This person should be able to work independently and have a drive for excellence.
 
·       Should be able to develop and execute database queries and conduct analyses. This person must be able to communicate well verbally and written and must exercise the importance of documentation.
 
·       This person should be at near expert level with SQL and be familiar with concepts like common table expressions, RANK, CASE, sub-queries, etc.
 
·       Must be familiar with pulling data out of data warehouse Dim/Fact tables as well as unstructured data and 3rd party data and marrying them together to get an overall view of the business.
 
·       A couple of years of SSRS experience is necessary with detailed understanding of expressions, data driven subscriptions, drill-down, drill-through, sub-reports, parameters, and report objects like tables, matrix, charts, maps, etc.…
 
·       Familiarity and some experience with PowerPivot are needed including creating data visualizations to support business monitoring, complex DAX expressions, and performance tuning PowerPivot and Tabular data models. Some experience with Qlik Sense, Power View, Essbase, SAS and visual analytics tools are nice to haves.
 
Required Skills
 
·       4+ SQL
·       4+ SSRS Report Development (experience with other vendor tools will be considered)
·       2+ PowerPivot, Power View, Qlik Sense, SharePoint, DAX
·       2+ Data warehouse experience (IBM Netezza – Pure Data for Analytics)
·       Experience with Qlik Sense and Essbase is a plus.

 ABOUT COTTONWOOD 
Founded in 1996, Cottonwood Financial is one of the largest privately held retail consumer finance companies in the consumer finance industry.  We have zero debt, have been profitable every year since inception, and our growth is funded entirely through internally generated capital.  Headquartered in Irving (Las Colinas), Texas, we have company-owned locations, under our Cash Store brand, across the country.  Through this national brick-and-mortar footprint, we provide best-in-class customer service and offer an innovative mix of financial products and services to our customers.

We have been named several times to the Inc. 5000 list of America’s fastest-growing private companies, as well as to the Dallas 100 list of the fastest-growing private companies in North Texas.

In addition, the Business Intelligence Team Lead serves as the team leader for BI programming staff and BI Analysts within the Business Intelligence team.Essential Duties and Responsibilities 
Working in collaboration with the VP of IT, project managers and business leads, oversees the BI project portfolio to ensure work is getting done timely and to quality standards; projects are appropriately aligned with agency goals and resources are allocated as needed
Researches/evaluates and makes recommendations for new BI technology and tools that are aligned with the agency's strategic goals and tactically improve business intelligence efficiency and effectiveness in meeting the needs of customers and stakeholders
Responsible for managing a BI team of 4 people; provides supervision and oversight to the BI team including BI analysts and BI programmers; this includes performance management, goal setting, planning and issue resolution within the department. This also includes developing standards and processes to enhance the overall BI service provided to the agency and its stakeholders
Works in collaboration with IT department to standardize department tools and cross train programmers to cover diverse areas/systems of the agency (i.e., helps eliminate silos of knowledge / expertise)

Serves as champion, trainer and mentor for BI super-users to equip them with tools and techniques to do their own querying of key data sets pertinent to their role in the agency
Reviews, analyzes, documents and evaluates end user data/reporting needs and recommends/implements solutions
Drafts detailed reporting requirements and the steps/plan required to deliver the solution; works with project managers, analysts, stakeholders and programmers to deliver the solution
Plans and prepares documentation to outline assumptions and methodology used to arrive at BI solutions as part of the requirements gathering process and overall report development methodology
Serves as both project manager and doer managing the entire report/solution workflow to include gathering and documenting requirements, building and testing the solution and ultimately delivering and deploying the solution in the production BI environment.

The Sr. Data Analytics Engineer is responsible for leading the successful delivery of business intelligence information to the entire organization. details:
TEGNA is seeking an experienced and hands-on Senior BI Developer for the Business Intelligence department.  The ideal candidate will be responsible for BI ‘cradle-to-grave’ development, from acquiring and aggregating data from multiple sources, designing and building analytic data marts, to creating and prototyping reports and rich visualizations thus providing business users the ability to turn data into actionable information. This role requires a strong familiarity with transactional and data warehouse/ database concepts; strong SQL skills and the ability to build BI platforms from scratch. 6+ years of industry experience in all aspects of designing, developing and supporting Analytics/BI environments

A team player and self-starter with good communication skills and ability to work independently and as a part of the team

That can include anything from coding to testing to debugging to designing to implementing newly developed tools. A BI engineer spends a lot of time researching and planning solutions for existing problems within the company. BI engineers also are responsible for building OLAP, or online analytical processing. details:
Position: Sr. BI Product Owner
Location: Alpharetta, GA
Duration: Direct Hire, Perm

Our client is a leading innovator in the contact center industry, and their mission is to solve the real-time challenges facing contact centers. A long and growing list of enterprise centers use their SaaS platform to automate a wide range of intraday management processes. The platform and community continue to grow, as their customers continue to find value like significant cost reduction, employee performance and engagement improvements, and omni-channel service delivery benefits.

Synergis is seeking a Product Manager (BI). As the Business Intelligence Product Manager, you will be responsible for our client's strategy, roadmap and implementation of Business Intelligence and Reporting solutions. The successful candidate will have demonstrated full lifecycle product management experience bringing Business Intelligence, Analytics or related solutions to market. In this role, you will collaborate closely with customers, operations, engineering and services to understand business needs, identify solutions, and develop and execute on roadmaps. You will be equally comfortable acting as Product Manager and Product Owner. Familiarity with Contact Center processes and solutions is desired but not required. Your mission is to become the in-house expert and leader in this domain to guide the development of new functionality for both existing and potential customers, as well as guide the overall direction of our Business Intelligence roadmap.

Product Manager (BI) Responsibilities:
•                    Collaborate closely with customers and internal stakeholders to establish, socialize and implement product roadmaps.
•                    Serve as Product Manager, responsible for the Business Intelligence strategy and roadmap.
•                    Serve as Product Owner for our Business Intelligence scrum team.
•                    Manage product features and dependencies across multiple releases.
•                    Manage, prioritize and groom an active backlog for your products.
•                    Work closely with the architecture team, ensuring the system design and technology platform fulfills near and long-term product needs.
•                    Define and communicate requirements to the engineering and architecture design teams.
•                    Maintain the near and long-term product roadmap, communicating plans and decision making processes to management and other stakeholders.
•                    Be an expert and advocate for your products both within and outside the company.
•                    Work with Integration Managers, Customer Success, Customer Support, Customers and Sales teams to synthesize client feedback into actionable plans for your product(s).
•                    Ensure the highest quality product is delivered to customers.
•                    Stay up-to-date on contact center solutions to identify and evaluate new opportunities.
•                    Provide customer voice and context in product decisions.

Product Manager (BI) Required Education, Experience and Skills:
•                    To be considered for this challenging position, applicants must be able to demonstrate a majority of the following skills, knowledge and abilities:
•                    3+ years relevant job experience.
•                    A passion and understanding for how data informs business decisions.
•                    Excellent Agile knowledge, with a background in a Scrum environment, writing complex user stories and acceptance criteria, and managing team resources.
•                    Demonstrated experience as a Scrum Product Owner.
•                    Familiarity with JIRA, and preferably Portfolio for JIRA
•                    A communicator, able to work with different teams across the company and "translate" information between these groups.
•                    A strong technical acumen, especially as it relates to methods and solutions for large scale, high performance BI platforms.
•                    Big-picture understanding of the overall product direction and needs, with the drive and attention to detail that transforms that understanding into a reality.
•                    Strong analytical skills - able to provide creative solutions to complex problems within our integrated product suite.
•                    Ability to manage a high number of ongoing tasks and maintain an awareness of the current status for each project.
•                    Understanding of Big Data Best Practices and Technologies desirable.
•                    Knowledge of and experience with call center technologies is desirable.
•                    Experience or knowledge of predictive analytics solutions is an advantage.
•                    Excellent written and verbal communication skills
•                    Self-starter capable of working on projects independently
•                    Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, MIS, CIS, Electrical Engineering, Mathematics or equivalent

If you are interested in the Product Manager (BI) position, please contact Sarah Hodges at (678) 580-4061 or by e-mail at [Click Here to Email Your Resumé]

Synergis serves a myriad of clients across nearly all industries, from start-ups to Fortune 100 companies. The outcomes of these relationships are demonstrated in a growing list of more than 300 clients and industry recognitions by Inc. magazine and the Atlanta Business Chronicle. From its foundation in 1997, Synergis has been successfully recruiting and placing IT professionals in all areas of information technology. Recently named the Best Place to Work in Atlanta by the Atlanta Business Chronicle, Synergis has been successfully recruiting and placing IT professionals for over 10 years. For more information about Synergis, please visit the company website.

Synergis is an Equal Opportunity employer.

The Senior BI Analyst is responsible for significantly enhancing our BI users’ experience in the Cloud BI space. The Senior BI Analyst will be primarily focused on taking the Enterprise Data as Data Governance and Data analyst team prepare it - and embedding key visualizations and drill paths into web portals for internal and external consumption. This person will also work with data science leads to expose pertinent data results to our customers. The incumbent must have web skills as well as BI skills, excellent UI/UX skills and show an innovative career path that will assist Veolia in moving into newer BI technical models such as AI, Virtual Reality and other cutting edge BI models. We are looking for someone with high innovation and high energy to fill this critical role on the BI team. This role reports to the Manager of BI/Data Governance.Key Job Responsibilities
Drive user experience and value in the Enterprise Data tools and via embedding of visualizations into customer facing web portals
Perform web coding and JavaScript work to embed the BI tools into websites and other applications - developing a strategy for maintenance and upkeep of these solutions that will scale effectively over time
Employ UI/UX evaluations and strategies to ensure the user experience is fast to get answers, relevant and working with technologies like chat, mobile and other very current models of data interaction
Work closely with the Data Analysis/Data Advocate team to understand relevant data trends and create visualizations that help share those trends to the appropriate business users in the most effective workflow
Work with Salesforce team to push the analytics models effectively inside of Salesforce
Assist the governance team with creation and documentation of calculated fields and metadata
Manage and Monitor BI performance, usage trends and errors to ensure the enterprise BI tool is working at peak support for the user base
Create and enforce standards such as color schemes, logos, and a consistent look/feel throughout the enterprise data management tools
Assist team with Security required for the BI tools
Push cutting-edge user experiences 
Assist with end user training plans and rollouts
Work to blend external data lake and MDM data into transactional visualizations effectively
Push forward Geo-Locational BI considerably over the next year to enhance the relevance of cross-system data



7 years of IT experience
3 years in a BI technical leadership role
Demonstrated large-scale UI/UX success
Expert SQL skills
BI experience in BI using cloud DWH tools such as Redshift
Experience coding embedded analytics in applications such as SAP HANA, Salesforce, Maximo and others 
Expertise in JavaScript, HTML and web coding tools for BI
High energy with interest in rapid innovation and customer adoption
Experience with MDM based BI processes

details:
Purpose of the Position:

Responsible for providing analytic support across the organization to enable better data-driven decision making and planning by senior management. As part of the ‘Business Intelligence’ function, the Analyst will assist with:


Establishing an enterprise-wide approach to data management.
Improving information accessibility and horizontal information sharing across the organization.
Creating a unified and integrated view of our core data aligned with main institutional objectives.
Streamlining manual report generation through a combination of automation and outsourcing/offshoring.


Primary Duties and Responsibilities


Play key role in cross-functional reporting and analytics efforts across multiple business units.
Identify reporting needs and create/improve daily, weekly and monthly reports.
Assemble and summarize data, make presentations of findings, and provide recommendations for cost savings and process improvement to senior management.
Conduct trending, forecasting, predictive modeling to identify patterns and get to the root causes.
Develop and maintain reports and metrics to track employee performance management.
Document and update existing standard operating procedures, process maps and org charts.
Standardize cross-departmental data definitions, KPIs, and calculations.
Share knowledge, expertise and best practices with new and existing analysts throughout the company.
Demonstrates knowledge of, and carefully follows all applicable federal and state compliance requirements and regulations including those prescribed by the Department of Education, accrediting agencies, CIE, and internal UMA policies and procedures.
Effectively communicates compliance requirements to students and other staff as appropriate and quickly escalates any compliance concerns to the Compliance department.




Skills & Core Attributes Required:


Ability to synthesize large amounts of data into snapshots appropriate for senior management use.


Ability to analyze data and understand business needs to recommend additional or improved ways to view the business.


Experience with creating dashboards using BI Tools (i.e. PowerBI or Tableau)


Ability to work with SQL databases (i.e. T-SQL)


Detail and deadline oriented, flexible to rapid change.


Strong operational, organizational, analytical, and technical skills.


Analytical thinker/mind-set with proven ability to solve complex problems.


Excellent written and verbal communication skills, specifically an ability to communicate effectively with senior management.


Proven experience with MS office suite including Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Access


Advanced Excel (formulas, Pivot Tables, Charting/Visualizations, Reporting and Dashboard building experience, VBA a plus)


Demonstrated ability to learn new computer systems.


Experience with financial and operational modeling.


Forecasting and statistical modeling (i.e. R, SAS, SPSS)


Flexibility to work evenings and weekends as needed.


 
Education/Experience Required:
 

Minimum of 1-3 years of experience in business, process, and operations initiatives. Advanced math and statistical skills.


Education Industry and call center experience a plus.
Minimum of Bachelors degree in Business, Economics, Math, Accounting or Finance

title: Business Intelligence Analyst

details:
Job Description - Business Intelligence Specialist
Business Intelligence (BI) Specialist

The growing Data Analytics group is seeking a Business Intelligence (BI) Specialist to work on our BI software and systems. This includes integration with SQL and external databases, supporting BI solutions to end users and senior management.

We are looking for someone with an eye for data visualization to illustrate the big picture, but who is also capable of cleaning up and organizing legacy data sets as part of an overall process.  Organization and attention to detail are a must.  Experience with either the legal or insurance industries would be an asset, but not required.  If you enjoy working with a team, but also are comfortable working independently to accomplish your tasks and projects, we want to talk to you.  

Primary Responsibilities

Develop and automate processes and data for company-wise dashboards.
Prepare data visualizations for internal and external use, using Power BI, web tools and PowerPoint. 
Research, analyze, and gather information from a variety of sources, including vendor databases, primary sources, web site sources, and print.
Assist with data clean-up and organization of legacy system data.
Create and maintain the data dictionary.  
Train end users to use self-service BI tools.  

 
Required Skills

Demonstrated competence with Power BI, Cognos or other data visualization tools, including creating visuals, building dashboards & customizations.
Expertise in building data visualizations with a strong understanding of the appropriate chart types to use to highlight patterns in the data.
Ability to analyze user requirements and build front-end BI dashboards according to specifications.
Strong oral and written communication skills, including presentation and graphics skills (MS PowerPoint)
Strong Excel skills, including PowerPivot, pivot tables & cell calculations. 
Demonstrated ability with SQL, DAX, R and/or M.

 
Education and Experience

BA/BS in Computer Science or related field is preferable.  Equivalent combination of experience, education, certifications and training will be considered.
2-3 years of experience preferred.
title: Business Intelligence Specialist

details:
Business Intelligence Analyst - Sales Operations
Position Overview 
The Business Intelligence Analyst will be a knowledge expert on a specific portfolio of clients. They are responsible for the collection, analysis, business insight, and publication and reporting on key sales and operational data with the overall objective of improving sales and operational performance as well as providing a data input into the business strategy and objectives/target set by the business.   The effective collection, analysis and presentation of this data is critical to enhance the understanding of the business and to improve decision making short-term and long-term.

Responsibilities
The Business Intelligence Analyst 3 will provide data in an informative state on an as-needed basis as well as against a defined business agreement with internal customers.
Roles & goals will encapsulate some or all of the below: 

Provision of bookings & revenue performance analysis against Plan and Forecast
Report on key business metrics vs. targets – opportunity and revenue, production metrics by client, by center and by region, benchmark with conclusions
Compilation of Sales Center forecasts for Sales Center Head and/or senior sales managers
Supporting the finance and executive team in compiling performance metrics required for post qtr. end deep dive   
Weekly headcount validation vs. plan and forecasts – FTE and Cost
Various reporting requirements e.g. sales incentive tracking, Performance review statistics, surveys, security audits, and others as required
Accurate accruals and invoicing supporting finance calendar
Lead the target setting and quota setting process for the Sales Teams in the Region
As required support the global team in the compensation and payout process
Publish team specific dashboards/balanced scorecards with key metrics and conclusions
Support the Account Management team in compiling insightful client team performance presentations and dashboards
Supporting the Sales teams with data requirements for different planning and operational asks
Lead statistical analysis on performance to drive insights / recommendations for the Sales team
Work with the Data Services team with tools that Sales and Operations Services can use to extract data / insights for daily business management in an automated manner
Report on and track Revenue generating programs
Provide mentoring and technical guidance to Junior Analysts in a specific portfolio

Job Requirements 

4-6 years practical business experience (preferably supporting a sales organization)
Experience with Tableau and ability to provide a portfolio of work for previous Tableau reporting builds
Prior background in inside sales preferred
Proven ability to perform complex analysis such as regression, forecasting and probability modeling
Experience working on multiple CRM and/or Information data repositories as well as Business Intelligence software (SFDC and Business Objects a plus)
Proven ability to capture and document business and reporting requirements from multiple sources
Proven ability to coordinate and manage simultaneous data analysis requests of varying size & scope

Additional Skills

Ability to identify active ways to influence KPI movement positively
Can modify and create custom metrics/KPIs for replicating our client's needs
Meets project timelines consistently with minimal to no supervision
Knows how to set reasonable expectations for clients that are aggressive but achievable through thought leadership
Consistently is proactive in identify potential grey areas in tasks, calculations, data management, processes, etc. and works to bring why there is a believed gap with a suggested path to resolve
Excellent communication and presentation skills – written and verbal with an ability to convey complex information to a broad audience
Proven knowledge and effective use of MS office applications
Demonstrated high level of proficiency in Excel. Able to create strong templates and best practices in place for reusability across clients. Can create dynamic workbooks to drive a complex refresh process that others can diagnose, understand, and use
Able to manage multiple Director-level stakeholders, plus significant client contact
Strong interpersonal skills with ability to work independently and within a team

About ServiceSource
ServiceSource (NASDAQ:SREV) is a global leader in providing outsourced, performance-based revenue growth and customer success outcomes. ServiceSource’s Revenue-as-a-Service platform is designed to measurably accelerate customer ROI by helping companies to more efficiently and effectively find, convert, grow and retain their B2B customer relationships. Trusted by more than 65 global market leaders in the cloud/XaaS, software, technology hardware, healthcare & life sciences and industrial sectors, ServiceSource sells, manages or renews $9+ billion of revenue annually on behalf of its clients. By leveraging a robust technology suite, predictive data models and more than 3,000 revenue delivery professionals, only ServiceSource brings to market over 15 years of expertise and the ability to drive recurring revenue growth in 35 languages to more than 170 countries. To learn more, visit http://www.servicesource.com.

NSC Technologies is currently hiring Enterprise Business Intelligence for immediate work in Charlotte, NC. 

This position requires that the candidate understands, uses and applies technical standards, principles, theories, concepts and techniques and provides solutions to a variety of technical problems of moderate to high scope and complexity. The candidate will also regularly interact with the customers to understand, document and communicate their needs, perform requirements analysis, develop and deliver reports and dashboards as per the requirements and contribute to the development and delivery of user training and documentation. The candidate will work under the general direction of the manager or the principal Systems Analyst and will independently determine and develop approach to solutions. The candidate will follow established procedures and contribute to the completion of milestones associated with specific projects and keep up-to-date with the technology shifts through training.
 

Reporting Hourly Pay: $40 per hour. Work week: Monday-Friday 8-5pm. Weekly Pay! 


·         5+ years of experience working in information technology industry

·         Strong interpersonal skills

Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems or similar

details:
We’re all in at DoubleDown.  Are you?The Business Intelligence department consists of ten people – developers and data scientists – who work and have fun together and are responsible for providing information and insights from our massive data sets. This information enables DoubleDown to understand our business, our players, and our games and helps us grow our business.DoubleDown is seeking to hire a Big Data Engineer to support our growing workload and to provide additional capabilities including machine learning and predictive analytics.We utilize many AWS products including RedShift, S3, Glue, Lambda, and Elastic Map Reduce to create and manage our state-of-the-art multi-Terabyte Enterprise Data Warehouse solution. Our team is a very-closely knit learning-oriented group who contribute greatly to the company’s success and has the opportunity to develop a wide range of technical and interpersonal skills and interact directly with our customers to deliver solutions that work well and are useful.We also have a lot of fun and even have a BI rap video to prove it!Roll the diceWe're DoubleDown Interactive, a talented team of approximately 170 Software Engineers, Game Designers, Artists, Producers, Marketers, Analytical Experts, and more.  Located in Seattle’s International District, we create fun, authentic casino-style entertainment via free-to-play social and mobile games, enjoyed by millions of players worldwide. As a leader in the social casino space, we continue to revolutionize through constant innovation. Known for our fun and collaborative culture, we move quickly to deliver exciting online game experiences to casino enthusiasts and social gamers alike!What you should bring to the table 
Bachelors or Master of Science, in Computer Science or other IT-related major
3-5 years of ETL experience in data warehousing or transactional systems
Proficient in at least one programming language (Java, Perl, Python, etc.)
Understanding and implementation experience or coursework with both relational and data warehousing models including star-schema, dimensional design, data mart, and database architecture

Strong problem solving and analytical skills; excellent communication skills
Winning the jackpotBy the end of your first year, you will be making major contributions to the EDW as demonstrated by:
Creation of rock solid ETL processes and SQL queries that populate the EDW
Successful support of BI analysts and data-hungry people in other parts of DoubleDown with data to support their reporting needs 
Placing your best bet - the responsibilitiesIn this high-visibility role reporting to the Director of Business Intelligence, the candidate will:
Create detailed specs for ETL design/development/support and then transform those designs into system capabilities utilizing standard coding tools and processes Work with end users to identify their ad hoc and scripted reporting needs
Maintain and streamline the existing data flow to improve accuracy and efficiency
Stay current with technical best practices and industry trends and advise and educate management on their importance
Instill a strong customer service and business-oriented ethic when working with both the team and end users
Identify and fix defects and reuse existing software components
Other cards you might be holding
Experience with Amazon Web Services (AWS)
Experience in one of the reporting tools such as Tableau, Talend, Business Objects, etc.
ETL experience in data warehousing or transactional systems
Cashing in on the comps
Getting to the office is a breeze with one of our two company-sponsored transportation options: 
ORCA pass, renewed annually
$100 monthly transportation credit


Stow your ride safely in the secured parking garage or bike locker available onsite. 
It’s a gaming company, so take a gaming break and get to know your coworkers with a little competitive fun! Square off over ping pong, foosball, or pinball in our arcade.  Like console games?  Challenge your coworkers to a Nintendo Wii U or Xbox 360 gaming break.  You’ll find plenty of takers for a tabletop gaming session, too!
Stay in tip-top shape by taking advantage of our onsite fitness center.  Just head down to the first floor of our building, and you’ll have access to state of the art equipment, lockers, and showers.  
Need to relax? Get a massage or enjoy a yoga session right here in the studio! After all, who wants to work without a massage? 
Enjoy occasional afternoons off for private viewings of first-run movies and team outings to see the Mariners play.
Hungry? Head to one of our two kitchens fully stocked with snacks and beverages.
You’ll never want to take the day off on Wednesdays, when we even provide a gourmet breakfast. 
Want to go out to lunch sometimes, too? Our International District location is perfectly situated near a variety of excellent restaurants. 
As if all of this isn't cool enough, you'll love our benefit package. 
We offer medical, dental, vision, prescription coverage, maternity/paternity leave, and disability protection (short- and long-term). 
Every team member receives 15 days of vacation, 40 hours of sick time, 2 personal floating holidays, and 11 paid calendar holidays per year.
Combine all of this with our amazing work/life balance and company-matched retirement options, and you have the dream job!

Conceptualize, design and develop data visualization solutions that synthesize data concepts into clear communications for key business stakeholders. Drive adoption of data and insights-driven business decision making processes and analytics-enabled business process innovation. Collaborate with data engineers and analytics and subject matter experts to identify useful and strategically relevant insights. Demonstrate a strong sense of visual design and interest in creative visualization work. Assist in developing best practices for data presentation and sharing across the organization. Demonstrate an ability to know and understand the audience and the information the audience needs. Demonstrate an ability to reduce data to the bare minimum of what is needed to optimally communicate a message. Demonstrate a drive to learn new tools and new ways of visualizing/displaying data and insights. Work closely with business users, vendors and delivery teams to understand the business requirements that drive the analysis and design of business analytics and reporting solutions. Show strong team building and creative thinking skills, and a desire to make a difference.   Preferred Qualifications  Bachelor’s degree in Programming/Systems or Computer Science or other related field. Or equivalent work experience. 5-10 years of experience in developing business analytics solutions, focusing on requirements gathering and effective visualization of insights. 5-10 years of experience with data visualization/BI tools, such as Qlik View, Qlik Sense a must. Tableau, SQL and semantic data access mechanisms. Experience in driving analytics-enabled business process innovation. Has a broad level of understanding surrounding business information systems. Experience in leading small project teams and streams. Demonstrated ability to analyze and interpret complex problems or processes that span multiple business areas, identify and understand requirements, and develop alternate solutions. Experience designing, developing and testing business.

details: Job SummaryThe Senior Analyst – Clarity ETL & BI Administrator is responsible for the enhancement and effective operations of the Epic Clarity environments at Stanford Health Care (SHC) including: Manage and administer the Epic Clarity environments and associated Extract, Transformation, and Load (ETL) processes. Implement new tables and ETL processes as requested by Reporting Teams and other Clarity users. Apply Epic Upgrades and SU’s to Clarity environments and manage impacts upon Clarity processes and users. Manage production promotion process and define effective release management procedures. Coordinate with Infrastructure teams to develop/execute an Infrastructure Roadmap including: hardware replacement cycles, system software upgrade plans, and hardware maintenance windows and procedures. Provide effective and timely communications to users and CBA team members of system downtime, outages, and issues. Define and manage all security and compliance processes related to PHI and other sensitive data within the Clarity environments. In addition, this role participates in the administration and support of the SAP BusinessObjects and Qlikview Business Intelligence (BI) environments used to produce Clarity Reports from the Clarity and other databases at SHC. This includes the following: Develop/modify Clarity Reports as prioritized and assigned. Promote new/modified reports to production environment and schedule report for execution and distribution to users. Perform security administration of users and access rights to reports. Essential Functions Manages production operations of Clarity ETL processes and periodically assess and actively manages overall performance, areas for optimization, Delay Build backlog, Backfill processing, etc. Coordinates with Epic Application Support, EDW/Caboodle, and Reporting Teams and vendor to review vendor release notes and implement changes/additions to Clarity data models and associated ETL in response to Epic build and configuration changes, upgrades and SU's. Develops and optimizes highly stable and maintainable ETL and Reporting solutions that meet user needs. Prepares clear and complete complex specifications, designs, test plans, and operations documentation. Manages creation, use and period refresh of various Clarity development and test environments. Coordination with Infrastructure teams to plan and test system and hardware maintenance. Provide effective and timely communications to users and CBA team members of system status (including Delayed Build and Backfill data), downtime, outages, and issues that may impact delivery of reporting to users and/or productivity of other teams. Understands and applies HIPAA standards and regulations to all areas of work. Define and manage appropriate security and compliance processes related to PHI and other sensitive data within the Clarity environments, including: system and database level security measures, SQL access logging and monitoring, etc. Develops on call schedules and procedures that clearly identify criteria for when on call resources are and are not to be contacted during nights and weekends. Coordinate with Infrastructure, Help Desk, and other teams to implement these on call procedures.  Troubleshoots incidents surrounding supported solutions, including after-hours escalations of major incidents, in compliance with SLA’s. Contributes to work effort & timeline estimation of projects and assists project managers in setting and meeting user expectations. Manages individual priorities and tasks to meet such timelines and actively contributes to project status reporting processes to identify and mitigate risks. Job Qualifications:Minimum Qualifications Education: BS/BA in information technology or business-related field from an accredited college or university. Certifications: Certification in Epic Clarity ETL Administration and at least one Epic Clarity Data Model (or equivalent experience reporting from an electronic medical database).Experience: Four (4) years of experience with design and development of BI solutions and/or administration of BI tools. Preferred Experience also includes the following: -3 years of experience with Epic Clarity ETL Console (preferably in a Unix environment) and responsibility for definition and implementation of ETL strategy, standards, error handling, logging and alerting, scheduling and job control.  -1 years of experience administering SAP Business Objects reporting (i.e., promotion of reports, scheduling reports, and distribution of reports).  -2 years of experience developing Epic Clarity Reports using Crystal Reports or WebIntelligence  -7 years of experience with database development (SQL Server and Oracle) and Structured Query Language (SQL).  -4 years of IT experience with health care provider organizations and a broad range of healthcare provider datasets (i.e., ADT, Orders, Encounters/Visits, Billing, etc.).  -5 years of project management experience, including technology evaluation and procurement, options assessments, and cost/benefit analyses.  Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities: -Demonstrated proficiency with Epic Clarity ETL Console.  -Demonstrated proficiency with database management systems (preferably Oracle) as well as Structured Query Language (SQL) and procedural languages (Pl/SQL, etc.) in Oracle.  -Demonstrated proficiency in Data Definition Language (DDL), Data Manipulation Language (DML), and Extraction, Transformation and Loading (ETL) design and development using Oracle (Pl/SQL) and/or SQL Server tools (SQL Management Studio, T-SQL, SSIS, etc.).  -Strong understanding of, and proficiency in, project management principles and best practices.  -Experience managing work queues of Incidents and Requests under one or more leading IT Service Management solutions, preferably ServiceNow.  -Deep experience implementing, ETL principles and best practices, including error handling, logging & alerting, scheduling and job control.  -Proficient in tuning performance of complex database structures, queries and procedures to optimize ETL performance and user query response times.  -Demonstrated proficiency with Business Intelligence (BI) tools and best practices (preferable SAP BusinessObjects or Qlik products).  -Thorough understanding of data architecture and database designs (ERD Diagrams).  -Strong writing and presentation skills that facilitate user requirements/design discussions, design reviews, user training sessions, and knowledge transfer to production support.  -Basic understanding of various quality and performance improvement methodologies as applied in a healthcare setting.  -Experience developing BI solutions that utilize healthcare data, preferably from Electronic Medical Record systems or other healthcare provider systems.  All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, sex, color, religion, national origin, protected veteran status or on the basis of disability.  #LI-AL1 ~LI~

details:
Alexa is Amazon's digital assistant, it's a cloud service that powers devices like Echo, Dot and Spot. Our team provides data and analytics across Alexa to help improve question answering, smart home device control, music control, and other experiences. 7+ years professional experience

Experience coordinating product development cycles and software development schedules

Demonstrated ability to coordinate projects across functional teams, including engineering, IT, product management, marketing, finance, and operations

Demonstrated ability to understand and discuss technical concepts, manage trade-offs and evaluate opportunistic new ideas with internal and external partners

History of teamwork and willingness to roll up your sleeves to get the job done
Experience in consumer-facing industry

details:
Business Intelligence Analyst – Revenue Cycle Clinical Operations – Maitland 
Florida Hospital seeks to hire a Business Intelligence Analyst who will embrace our mission to extend the healing ministry of Christ. 


Facility Profile: 
Established in 1908, Florida Hospital is one of the largest not-for-profit healthcare systems in the country, caring for more than a million patients each year. The Maitland Office Plaza houses our highly skilled teams that support our hospital system including Marketing, Patient Financial Services, Revenue Management, the Credit Union and Human Resources. The Trickel Building, a two-story office structure, creates an atmosphere of health and healing, with a healthy-style café and quaint chapel. The main lobby is filled with lush greenery and a light trickle of water, creating a holistic environment. 


Work Hours/Shifts: 
Monday – Friday; 8a – 5p 


Job Summary: 
Under general direction, performs a wide range of duties to analyze, produce and compile routine and specific reports of past, present, and future statistics/trends for the benefit of management and operational decision making. Interacts with Senior Finance Officers, Revenue Cycle Directors and Assistant Directors. Performs research, collects data, and skillfully organizes and presents the analysis to management in written and/or oral format. Adheres to Florida Hospital Corporate Compliance Plan and all rules and regulations of all applicable local, state and federal agencies and accrediting bodies. Actively participates in outstanding customer service and accepts responsibility in maintaining relationships that are equally respectful to all. 


Knowledge, Skills, Education, & Experience Required: 

Ability to use discretion when discussing personnel/patient related issues that are confidential 
Ability to be responsive to ever-changing matrix of hospital needs and act accordingly 
Ability to analyze fairly complex computer related problems within the department and perform effectively while working within tight time constraints 
Proficiency in performance of basic math functions and capable of communicating professionally with use of English and spelling 
Ability to compile and analyze information on trended data 
Ability to work in a project-oriented environment with people of various backgrounds 
Proficiency in creating statistical spreadsheets using macros and formulas, and has expert knowledge of Excel, PowerPoint, Word, Business Objects and Structured Query Language (SQL) 
Ability to work in a fast-paced, dynamic environment, and meet deadlines 
Ability to present information to all levels of management 
Ability to relate operational and financial performance in the healthcare environment and utilize basic knowledge of healthcare payment methods 
Critical thinking skills and ability to exercise objective, independent judgment in developing financial recommendations for management 
Self-motivated, with a detail-oriented focus, and outstanding customer service skills 
Knowledge of Florida Hospital Information Systems, including Suncare, Cerner, Qlikview and Query Management Facility (QMF) (Preferred) 
Knowledge of coding, Care Management, Utilization Management, Readmissions, Post-Acute Placement, and population health (Preferred) 
Bachelor’s degree in Accounting, Business Management, Economics, Finance, Healthcare Management, Hospitality Management, Nursing or a healthcare/business related field, OR 
Three to four (3-4) years of progressive healthcare experience in business/clinical analytics or equivalent 
Master’s degree in related business or healthcare field (e.g., MBA, MHA, MPH or MSN) (Preferred) 



Licensure, Certification, or Registration Required: 

Current, active State of Florida license as a Registered Nurse (Preferred) 



Job Responsibilities: 
Demonstrates through behavior Florida Hospital’s Core Values of Integrity, Compassion, Balance, Excellence, Stewardship and Teamwork as outlined in the organization’s Performance Excellence Program 

Meets deadlines for established goals in an accurate and efficient manner in all aspects of projects. 
Analyzes reports and existing customer scorecards to discern trends and potential areas of improvement. 
Provides vital feedback to operational owners on performance enhancement and works with end users to optimize areas of opportunity. 
Responsible for creating and maintaining overall operational reports to be used as tools to make vital decisions as requested from Management and Adventist Health System Corporate Directors or Florida Hospital Administration. 
Creates queries and compiles weekly, monthly and quarterly reports timely and effectively using Structure Query Language (SQL)/Business Objects interface as requested by Senior Management. 
Compiles weekly, monthly or quarterly reports such as length of stay, Diagnosis-Related Group (DRG) case mix, readmissions and more. 
Develops and deploys plans to ensure department productivity and/or continued progress towards goals. Follows up with operational owners to address any concerns with sustainability of reports or projects. 
Performs wide range of duties in support of total department efficiency 
Remains current with all assigned reading and department Computer Based Learning (CBL) education plans. 
Facilitates smooth and efficient operation of department by being available and prepared to work during scheduled working hours and attends meetings as requested by management. Willing to seek extra work, accepts new responsibilities, and adapts to potential departmental change. Accepts and profits from direction and constructive feedback. Prioritizes multiple projects, meets project deadlines, and manages multiple customer relationships. 

If you want to be a part of a team that is dedicated to delivering the highest quality in patient care, we invite you to explore the Business Intelligence Analyst opportunity with Florida Hospital and apply online today.

At AIM Specialty Health (AIM), a proud member of the Anthem, Inc. family of companies,  it’s a powerful combination, and the foundation upon which we’re creating greater care for our members, greater value for our customers, and greater health for our communities. Join us and together we will drive the future of health care. This is an exceptional opportunity to do innovative work that means more to you and those we serve. 

 
 
Our analytics team is seeking a Business Intelligence Developer (Business Information Consultant) to be responsible for the development of business intelligence tools such as interactive reporting, dashboard design, and data visualization. We work in a fast-paced environment that is hungry for analytics and insights. Consult with business stakeholders to provide analytics and business intelligence for data-driven decision making.

About AIM Specialty Health
AIM Specialty Health (AIM) is a leading specialty benefit management company that promotes appropriate, safe and affordable healthcare services.  We are a member of the Anthem family of companies, which is recognized as one of the nation’s leading health benefits companies.
 
AIM provides innovative clinical solutions that focus on today’s most complex and costly tests and treatments in radiology, cardiology, medical and radiation oncology, specialty drugs, sleep medicine, musculoskeletal and pain management, genetic testing, palliative care, and other emerging clinical areas. 
 
With evidence-based medicine, technology, people and processes, we support clinical appropriateness review, provider collaboration and member engagement on behalf of more than 50 health plans, 40% of the Fortune 50 Employers, and 43 million members.
 
Today, our team includes more than 1,100 associates and features more than 600 licensed and board-certified physicians, nurses, and other healthcare professionals who engage with more than 330,000 health care providers across the country. These healthcare providers access our solutions and specialized clinical expertise through our online ProviderPortal and experienced contact center-based teams that is enabled by our business platform.  
 
Our pioneering spirit and dedication to improve health care continues to produce significant industry-first advancements, quality recognition achievements, and high satisfaction rates.  AIM is certified by the National Committee for Quality Assurance (NCQA) and has received Full Accreditation for Health Utilization Management from the Utilization Review Accreditation Commission (URAC.)
 
We maintain offices in Chicago, Deerfield, Schaumburg and Westchester, IL, as well as Glendale, CA.  
 
To learn more, visit http://www.aimspecialtyhealth.com/.

details:
Ardagh Group is a global leader in glass and metal packaging solutions, producing packaging for the world’s leading food, beverage and consumer care brands. Ardagh Group has a truly global presence. We operate 109 glass and metal manufacturing facilities in 22 countries, employing approxmately 23,500 people and have global sales of approxmately US$8.2 bn.
 
At Ardagh we have a reputation for innovation; pushing the boundaries of what’s possible, pioneering new production methods, new design techniques and new ways to recycle and save energy. The unprecedented growth of our business has been driven by our unrivalled expertise, obsession with quality and commitment to continuous improvement.
 
We strongly believe that the success of our business depends on the success of our people. We strive to create working environments where our employees feel valued, can work to their full potential and where their achievements are celebrated. We are creating an exciting future for Ardagh that is built on our core values of trust, teamwork and excellence and we have opportunities in a wide variety of disciplines across our organization.
 
For more information on Ardagh Group, please visit www.ardaghgroup.com
You can also download our News Centre App by searching Ardagh in the App Store.

As a member of Ardagh Group’s Global Business Intelligence team, the Business Intelligence Analyst is responsible for the analysis, design, development and maintenance of the company’s business intelligence platform.  This position will have a key role in the execution of the company’s global business intelligence strategy.

Essential Duties

Organize and lead business intelligence projects designed to enhance the organization’s reporting and analytical effectiveness.
Meet with key stakeholders to gather requirements and design data models and reporting objects to meet functional and technical needs.
Design and develop dashboards using modern visualization tools.
Troubleshoot and resolve BI system and data loading related issues.
Provide formal and informal training and mentoring to end user groups on the effective use of the business intelligence toolset.
Manage BI system security and authorization models.


Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in systems, engineering, computer science or a related discipline, or a business degree combined with appropriate technical skills.
Strong understanding of business intelligence architectures and methodologies.
Minimum 5 years’ experience developing and supporting business intelligence solutions.
Minimum 2 years’ experience developing SAP BW ETL processes and dimensional modeling.
Minimum 2 years’ experience working with Business Objects reporting toolsets.
Strong project management skills with demonstrated ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously.
Strong verbal & written communication skills are required.
Ability to work independently and in a team environment under tight deadlines.


Preferred Qualifications

Strong SQL skills.
Experience working with a global, multinational BI team supporting a global BI implementation.
Experience working with and supporting BI on SAP Hana database.
Experience with SAP Lumira 2.0 and Design Studio.
Experience with creating of complex BODS jobs, work flows and scripts. 


Our Vision and Values
The people that make up Ardagh Group share much more than a strong brand and an excellent reputation. We each share a common vision: to be the preferred packaging partner to the world’s leading brands. We will achieve our vision by delivering customer innovation, providing an inspirational environment for our people and creating sustainable value for our business through its growth and development.

title: Analyst, Business Intelligence

details:
Description  JOB SUMMARYThis job plans, designs, tests and implements Business Intelligence solutions through use of BI tools, technologies and systems. Analyzes complex processes and develop technical and/or process solutions to meet business needs.  The incumbent works collaboratively with customers and technical staff in all phases of projects, potentially including requirements gathering and change management. Acts as subject matter expert on projects regarding technology, resource needs, schedule and/or implementation. Follows all divisional and corporate project management guidelines.This position will be responsible for the administration, development, and design of data integration processes.  The data integration processes will include ingestion, transformation, and extraction following a standardized enterprise data architecture.  They will be responsible for supporting day to day needs as well as working as part of project teams on larger initiatives.  This person will deliver services for data quality, master data management, EDI, and ETL.  This person will take requirements from various IT and business groups around data needs and work with external vendors to extract and ingest data files.  Some of the core competencies needed for this role include requirements gathering (type of data, file layout, etc.), testing, data quality, and data validation.     ESSENTIAL RESPONSIBILITIES
Design, develop, implement and maintain of Business Intelligence (BI) solutions to support business needs, following BI development best practices and innovative use of appropriate technologies and systems.  
Work collaboratively with business management and staff to deliver technical solutions that meet customer needs.  
Work effectively with customers in all phases of application development projects, potentially including requirements gathering, design, testing and change management.  
Provide end user support for BI solutions and applications, including investigation and resolution of issues regarding tool functionality and performance.    
Keep abreast of new BI and related technology and trends and assess when and if new technology is needed.  
Participate in quality or process improvement activities, including regular reviews of systems and technology.  Design and implement modifications or improvements, based on those activities.    
Provide input on strategies and tactics regarding platforms, tools and technical staffing to meet customer needs.  
Provide input to business cases, contracts, project plans, scope of work, status and project summary reports.
Follow and/or support prescribed project management guidelines.  Project management responsibilities include documentation of design and technical testing, as well as managing and negotiating project scope, timelines and developing/defining project deliverables with business customers.   
Provide guidance and direction to other staff and may function as a team leader.  
Train employees, assign, monitor and review progress and accuracy of work.   
Other duties as assigned or requested.
MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS:
Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, Math or other related area or 6 years experience in lieu of degree
5 years of work experience
PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS:
4+ years of ETL experience
2+ years using Informatica
1+ years EDI experience(HIPAA preferred)
5+ years SQL/PLSQL experience
Experience in enterprise data flow and architecture
Experience in data warehousing and data modeling
Health care industry experience

title: Business Intelligence - Analytics Developer

details:
SENIOR DATA ENGINEER (SSIS/SSAS/SSRS)
 
PROJECT DETAILS
LOCATION: Chicago, IL       
START DATE: ASAP
LOA: 6 month+ contract
 
PROJECT DESCRIPTION
TPA Technologies is seeking a Senior Data Engineer.  Our Digital Technology client has an immediate need for a Senior Data Engineer.  As a Senior Data Engineer, you’re responsible for proposing, designing, and implementing technical solutions to improve our clients’ data-driven insight capabilities.
 
These solutions encompass all aspects of development for data analytics solutions from front end data visualization and backend data management, including modern data architecture, data integration, and Master Data Management (MDM). The ideal candidate will also have experience with tools and techniques surrounding ETL/MDM, Business Intelligence (specifically, Microsoft Business Intelligence solutions using SSIS, SSAS and SSRS) Data Visualization, Analytics, and Big Data.
 
You are expected to be involved in the full lifecycle of delivering projects, from creation and review of proposals with the sales team, to accountability for delivery of customized solutions that deliver long-term value to our clients. You are ideally a thought leader and have a perspective as to the evolution and future of information management.

RESPONSIBILITIES
·         Serve as lead in delivery and oversight, define solutions, plan information management projects, and provide extensive technical and strategic guidance to project team members
·         Ensure best practices and standards are adhered to across Data Warehousing and Business Intelligence (specifically, Microsoft Business Intelligence solutions using SSIS, SSAS and SSRS) projects
·         Conduct and lead white-boarding sessions, workshops, design sessions, and project meetings, playing a key client-facing role for the project
·         Partner closely with business users to identify and analyze requirements
·         Understand clients’ operations and business processes to design and recommend end-to-end information management solutions, including database design/structures, data integration and reporting frameworks
·         Evaluate potential technology/tool solutions that meet business needs, and facilitate discussions toward desirable outcomes
·         Create functional and technical documentation related to data architecture and business intelligence solutions
·         Effectively diagnose, isolate, and resolve complex problems pertaining to data infrastructure, including performance tuning and optimization
·         Define solution roadmaps to achieve end-state solutions, including capability prioritization and cost estimates
·         Review project communications and deliverables to ensure consistent, high-quality client project experience
·         Engage with client senior leadership to build rapport, address strategic concerns, and translate complex technical terminology and concepts to an appropriate level (e.g. explain to non-technical staff)
·         Follow technology and industry trends and educate sales and solutions teams on new developments that will impact existing or potential clients
·         Work with pre-sales teams to develop proposals and pricing models for complex and innovative customer solutions

·         Review and assess technical proposals and contracts, validating feasibility of technical approach/design and rationalizing effort and resource estimates
 
ABOUT TPA TECHNOLOGIES
TPA technologies, formerly known as The Professional Alternative, is a solutions partner serving the Information Technology needs of Corporate America and Government Business partners. We utilize methodologies developed over 10 years to provide "Best Fit" solutions. A proven leader in identifying technical professionals best suited to have an immediate and positive impact on the needs of our clients' requirements. Business partners are provided with the ability to obtain desired results and the flexibility required to ensure cost effective solutions.

·         We are actively looking for professionals with experience in the following Enterprise Information Management disciplines:
 
DATA WAREHOUSING
·         Data Warehouse Design and Architecture
·         Data Mart Design and Architecture
·         Dimensional Modeling
·         Data Integration/Data Services
 
ANALYTICS AND REPORTING
·         Performance Management
·         Balanced Scorecards & Dashboards
·         Ad hoc and Guided Analytics / OLAP
·         Predictive Analytics
·         Data Visualization
 
DATA GOVERNANCE
·         Design and Initiation of Data Governance Organization
·         Design and Initiation of Data Governance Process
·         Metadata Management
·         Master Data Management
·         Data Quality
·         Data Auditing and Security
 
PREFERRED SKILLS
·         Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or related
·         5+ years of experience designing and implementing Microsoft Business Intelligence solutions using SSIS, SSAS and SSRS
·         5+ years of progressively responsible, post-baccalaureate experience in Business Intelligence (specifically, Microsoft Business Intelligence solutions using SSIS, SSAS and SSRS) or Data Management, architecting and implementing enterprise data and analytic solutions
·         3+ years of experience leading Data Warehousing/Business Intelligence (specifically, Microsoft Business Intelligence solutions using SSIS, SSAS and SSRS) implementation teams, managing project scope, providing technical leadership, and mentoring junior resources
·         3+ years of experience with database design, from conceptualization to database optimization, using common cloud and on-prem platforms, such as AWS Redshift, Azure SQL Data Warehouse, BigQuery, SQL Server, Teradata, Oracle, etc.
·         Deep experience or knowledge in foundational information management arenas, such as Master Data Management, Data Governance, Modern Data Architecture, and Data Integration
·         Experience in Data Architecture/Modeling, ETL, Data Quality and MDM tools, including IBM Infosphere and Microsoft SQL Server Integration Services, Data Quality Services, and Master Data Services
·         Experience in architecting and implementing emerging technologies/tools, such as AWS, Hadoop, Cloudera, and/or Hortonworks, to address predictive analytics and unstructured data use cases
·         Experience in designing and implementing Next Generation Architecture solutions incorporating Big Data, NoSQL, Cloud-Based Analytics, and Real-Time Analytics
·         Experience in working with large volumes of data from disparate data sources across complex business processes and functions
·         Must have strong leadership and interpersonal skills to resolve problems in a professional manner, lead working groups, negotiate, and create consensus
·         Must be able to astutely operate in and navigate through client organizations
·         Must have strong written/oral communication and presentation skills
·         Must be highly self-motivated, entrepreneurial, humble, and curious
