Job Description
Title
Sales Business Intelligence Specialist
Department
Commercial Support and Implementations
Scope
United States
JOB SUMMARY:
The Sales Business Intelligence Specialist reports into the Director of Commercial Support and Implementations. The Sales Business Intelligence Specialist will be part of an innovative Implementation Team that enables the enterprise to explore outliers and take actions that differentiate Agility Logistics from our competition. You will work closely with Sales leaders to understand, influence and capture business performance measures and its value to the organization. You will analyze data to make sure those measures can be properly tracked and work with other team members like data engineers and data architects to make sure transformed data is successfully available in data warehouse. This role requires creativity of dashboard design, problem solving, and analysis that demands excellent knowledge in Sales and Marketing analytics, supply chain management and can demonstrate best practices in the BI industry.
 
ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:
•         Work with business leaders across the enterprise to understand business questions that data can answer to provide data-driven insights
•         Support the sales quarterly business review process (QBR)
•         Facilitate design sessions with leaders to understand their business outcomes and what metrics enable them to track and monitor those outcomes.
•         Ensure accuracy, completeness and timeliness of reporting through proactive awareness, alerts, testing and processes
•         Drive new customer experience KPIs, metrics, tracking methodologies and data visualizations that provide complete customer journeys.
•         Work with large datasets to investigate key business trends, performance, issues, and behaviors
•         Create and manage dashboards, scorecards, and other analytical services for Sales, Marketing, and Customer Support organizations.
•         Integrate multiple data sources into one visualization to tell a story.
•         Design, build, enable and maintain dashboards and scorecards specifically for Customer Experience for both executive level and functional areas including mediums such as Tableau, Power Bi and Microsoft Excel
•         Collaborate across teams, geographies, and organizational levels to develop solutions that bring analytics into the business process
•         Communicate finding and insights to key stakeholders and influence these teams to take action based on your recommendations
•         Develop SharePoint solutions to manage key customer data and documents
•         Develop VBA solutions

QUALIFICATION AND EXPERIENCE:
Candidate should have at least 4 years of working experience in the freight forwarding and/or transportation industry. Have a sound working experience of various international transportation products. General knowledge of process flows and accounting practices would be an added advantage.
•                     Minimum of 3-5 years detailed analytics experience with Sales, services, and/or Marketing information
•                     Strong skills in dashboard development required, Power Bi, Tableau, Dundas is a plus
•                     Spent 2-3 years in business operations analytics team of Sales or Marketing or Customer Success or Support
•                     Knowledge of CRM and ability to operate as the point of contact for the business partner.
•                     Project management skills; demonstrated ability to manage technology projects.
•                     Strong verbal and written communication skills.
•                     Bachelor’s Degree in Business, Information Systems or related area.
•                     Added knowledge of VBA, C++ preferred but not mandatory
•                     Basic Supply Chain Management knowledge preferred
 
SKILLS & COMPETENCIES
•       Expertise with BI tools including Tableau to drive visualizations & industry best practice reporting
•       Exceptional ability to visually present and communicate data, analyses, and findings
•       Highly flexible, ability to execute well in a fast-paced, rapidly evolving organization
•       Knowledge of Voice of the Customer (VOC) analytic programs to integrate offline and online data to understand customer behavior including text analytics
•       Great attention to detail to ensure highest level of quality/rigor in reports & data analysis
•       Ability to meet deadlines and handle varying workloads with a high degree of accuracy
•       Proactive, organized, detail oriented, and quality driven
•       Ability to maintain discretion and confidentiality with sensitive employee information
•       Ability to identify, analyze, and resolve problems logically and systematically
•       Strong BI reporting knowledge to help drive automated systems
•       Ability to effectively communicate and translate business requirements to technical requirements
•       Statistical analysis a plus including correlation analysis, linear regressions, market basket analysis, etc.
Language
•       Spoken: English
•       Written: English

Internal interfaces: All stakeholders involved in internal and customer projects.
External interfaces: Customers, consultants, 3rd party providers, suppliers etc. that play a part in the supply chain.

STATEMENT OF NON-INCLUSIVITY:
This job description is not to be construed as a complete listing of the duties and responsibilities that may be given to any employee.  The duties and responsibilities outlined in this position may be added to or changed where deemed appropriate and when necessary by the person who is managerially responsible for this position.

This person will work within a team but will be responsible for servicing and managing the needs of their assigned clients.Essential Job Duties and Responsibilities 
Create analytics reports to provide valuable, relevant business insights for clients
Write ad-hoc T-SQL of a complex nature to support reporting needs
Identify, define, and prioritize customer requirements
Create indexes, tables, columns, and stored procedures as needed in our database environment
Provide customer service to new and existing clients
Maintain professional and technical knowledge by attending educational workshops; reviewing professional publications; establishing personal networks; participating in professional societies
Collaborate with developers, stakeholders and subject-matter experts to establish technical vision and analyze trade-offs between usability and performance needs Perform statistical analysis against data to develop models and identify trends in support of the business.
Implement and work with Microsoft Business Intelligence tools (SQL and Excel) and dashboard reports.

Microsoft SQL Server 2008 or above

title: Analyst II Business Intelligence

details:
Business Intelligence Analyst
Great opportunities await you at The Main Street America Group!  The Main Street America Group is a billion-dollar super-regional property & casualty insurance company, providing products in 36 states.
A newly created  Business Intelligence Analyst position is available data warehouse unit located at our Corporate Headquarters location in Jacksonville, Florida.    
The Business Intelligence Analyst is responsible for eliciting and defining requirements to refine and implement the enterprise business intelligence (BI) strategy and overall data warehouse ecosystem. Works  as a liaison among business operations, technology groups, business partners, vendors, and project management office to understand, analyze, and facilitate business needs, requirements, and impacts of business changes as a result of strategic initiatives, operational changes, compliance requirements, client needs, and technology or operational improvements.
Works on small to large projects ranging in complexity. Identify, analyze, specify and model BI needs and requirements as related to the Data Warehouse. Communicates and facilitates the activities and deliverables associated with business requirements, business processes, options and alternatives, validation and testing of solutions, training and implementation. Also provide ongoing support for existing and new BI solutions.
Responsibilities: 
• Work closely with the technical development team and business SME’s to clearly document source elements and ensure standardized values, formats, business rules/algorithms, meta data requirements, and data element relationships are understandable to the business customers and BI development group.
• Prepare for, conduct, and document requirement  sessions using a variety of techniques (Interviewing, requirements workshops/JAD sessions, reviewing existing documentation, etc…)
• Manage requirements traceability of requirements back to solution scope and objectives, and transforms business requirements to system requirements and testing
• Partner with the technical development teams to document the specifications for mapping and transformation rules all the way from source to target.
• Assess the proposed solution for alignment to business needs, requirements, and impacts to operations, processes, technology, vendors, business partners.
• Perform data extract and analysis using SQL on multiple database platforms
• Assess capability gaps, determine solution options and approach, and define solution scope
• Manage solution scope, changes to requirements, and requirements conflicts
• Verify and validate requirements with project team and stakeholders
Minimum Qualifications: 
• Bachelor’s degree or equivalent work experience
• 4+ years related work experience in business and systems analysis, specifically in a Data Warehouse environment
• 4+ experience extracting and analyzing data using SQL
• Experience and advanced understanding of relational and data warehouse DBMS environment. - Star schema, snow-flaking, slowly changing dimensions, aggregate table design and navigation, operational data stores, data marts, etc ..
• Demonstrated experience on large complex projects and eliciting requirements using a variety of techniques, in specifying and modeling requirements and in facilitating business process improvements, in problem solving, creative thinking, conflict management, and consensus building
• Established proficiency with Microsoft Office suite of programs
Preferred Qualifications:
• 3-5 years Property and Casualty Insurance experience
• Experience using multiple SDLC methodologies and best practices, preferably in the development of Data Warehouse  solutions
• Strong application and data modeling skills utilizing industry standard notations such as UML to design solutions for complex problems
• Data Stage and or Cognos is preferred. 
 
Not accepting H-1B or EAD candidates at this time.
Our benefit package includes:   

Medical, Dental & Vision (Day 1 coverage)
401(k) with Company Match
Pension Plan
Paid Time Off Program
Incentive (Bonus) Plan
Relocation Program
Employee Wellness Program (Health & Fitness)
Perks at Work Program (company discounts on travel, entertainment, electronics and apparel)
Paid Holidays
Company-Paid Disability and Life Insurance
Tuition Reimbursement Programs
Flexible Spending Accounts for Health & Dependent Care
Casual Dress Code

Visit our website for more information or to apply at  msagroup.jobs.net  /
Contingency Recruiters: Please do not send resumes directly to any hiring manager within the MSA organization.  If you would like to discuss this position, please contact the Staffing Department directly and NOT our managers. You must have a signed and current search agreement with the MSA Staffing Department before any resumes can be reviewed. Any resumes sent directly to MSA without a contract and specific work order in place for the position will be considered property of MSA.  Thank you for your cooperation in this matter!

Relationship Building - Initiates, develops, maintains, and strengthens partnerships with others inside or outside the organization.Drive for Results - Continuously focused on achieving/exceeding goals and objectives. Sets high standards of performance; pursues aggressive goals and works hard to achieve them.
title: Business Intelligence Analyst

details:
BI Analyst – Virtual all US locationsWe are currently seeking a seeking a Business Intelligence (BI) Analyst to join our BI & Analytics team. You will work closely with our platform BI manager and specialists to study formal and informal data to help better understand performance.  This is a great opportunity for an analytically minded individual willing to learn multiple service lines to use information to influence the decision making process. This is a virtual role but prefer Chicago, Philadelphia, Phoenix, Charlotte, San Francisco or Los Angeles.What this job involvesYou’ll need to have a great knowledge in Business Intelligence and be fluent in Technology. In this role, you will assess the current technical environment and develop technology requirements and conceptual solutions to meet business objective. You will partner with data owners to understand business requirements and common reporting/analysis use cases and work with technical and business teams to define appropriate technical solutions which includes BI solutions & data warehouse implementation, data access and dashboard creation. You will also be assisting with some reporting- drafting and distributing of reports.To be successful in this role, you should be a confident professional with broad skills in analyzing and solving complex business problems, writing and presenting, facilitating and influencing. This includes being able to extrapolate data and be able to forecast and trending of performance data as well as analyze trends of monthly Key Performance Indicator results for performance improvement concepts. Also, you should be able to provide hands-on support to provision data from a variety of internal sources, build reporting and meta-data models to support strategic data initiatives and design complex reports and dashboards based on requirements.Sound like you? Before you apply, it’s also worth knowing what we’re looking for:
A Bachelor's Degree in Engineering, Finance, Information Technology or related field is required; also along with 0- 2 years of experience in Corporate Real Estate environment.
Previous experience with other data and statistical applications are a plus (PowerPivot, Tableau, SAS, Access, MiniTab, Sigma Excel, SQL)
You’ll need to be dynamic and technologically savvy and utilize software to support planning solutions and communicate ideas clearly with planning team and lines of businesses. You will be successful if you have advanced skills in Microsoft Excel (pivot table, vlook-up, and cell calculations) and Sharepoint. Proficiency in Microsoft Office suite and ability to consolidate data into Power Point for presentations to client and lines of business is highly valued.
You’ll be effective in you role by learning to ask the right questions to understand the underlying needs of our clients. You’ll discover how to be proactive and innovative with solutions to your stakeholders.
Excellent communication skills are important – both written and spoken – and we’ll expect you to work independently, multi-task, and manage your time to meet deadlines. You’ll often need to reorganize your time day to day, to deal with your team’s changing necessities and requests.
An individual with strong interpersonal skills with an ability to interact with all levels of external and internal clients will be successful in the role. Most importantly, you’ll want to work as part of a diverse supportive and talented team.
What you can expect from us:You’ll join an entrepreneurial, inclusive culture. One where we succeed together – across the desk and around the globe. Where like-minded people work naturally together to achieve great things.Our Total Rewards program reflects our commitment to helping you achieve your ambitions in career, recognition, well-being, benefits and pay. We’ll offer you a competitive salary and benefits package.With us, you’ll develop your strengths and enjoy a career full of varied experiences. We can’t wait to see where your ambitions take you at JLL.Apply today!JLL Is an Equal Opportunity EmployerJLL is committed to developing and maintaining a diverse workforce.  JLL strongly believes in equal opportunity extended to all individuals in all aspects of the employment relationship, including recruitment, hiring, training, promotion, transfer, discipline, layoff, recall and termination without regard to race, color, religion, belief, creed, age, sex, pregnancy or maternity (including childbirth and related conditions), family responsibility (e.g. child care, elder care), nationality, ethnic or national origin or ancestry, citizenship, marital status, civil partner status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, transgender status, veteran’s status, genetic information, trade union membership, social position, political view or status as a qualified individual with a disability, protected leave status or any other protected characteristic in accordance with applicable law.  The company also endeavors to make reasonable accommodations for known physical or mental limitations of otherwise qualified employees and applicants with disabilities unless the accommodations would impose an undue hardship on the operation of our business and ensures that employment decisions are based only on valid job requirements.For employees in the United States, please see a fully copy of our Equal Employment Opportunity and Affirmative Action policy at https://jll2.sharepoint.com/CorporatePolicies/HR%20Policies/Equal%20Employment%20Opportunity%20and%20Affirmative%20Action.pdf.  If you have questions about careers at JLL or are disabled and require further assistance in applying for a position, please contact us at [Click Here to Email Your Resumé]
title: BI Analyst

details:
The newly formed Data Strategy and Governance team supports key functions across the business by utilizing innovative solutions to provide frictionless and timely access to high-quality, integrated data. The team consists of experts in data governance, data quality, data integration, data modeling, and data channeling, as well as reporting and dashboards. As the Senior Business Intelligence Analyst, You will be responsible for designing and building standard reports, dashboards, and data visualizations, using business intelligence tools like Tableau and MicroStrategy, to provide business insights for senior management and other stakeholders across Hilton. What will I be doing?As a Team Member in this role, you will be responsible for: 
Developing well-organized and insightful reports, dashboards, and other forms of data visualizations to support strategic, tactical and operational business decisions
Collaborating with the Data Integration and Architecture team in defining the architecture of data sources that will support reporting requirements
Working with the technical and functional teams to identify data anomalies and ensure report accuracy
Managing and supporting ad-hoc projects to provide business insights, intelligence, or business process efficiency and improvements
Providing training and support to end users on the use of the report and dashboard solutions
Gathering and validating reporting requirements (key data elements, report owners, objects, etc.) using functional design documents
Assisting in translating requirements into tangible deliverables and expected results for product, performance and user acceptance testing
Assisting with the data quality process to ensure the integrity of data sources consumed by reporting
Designing and implementing the reporting semantic layer used in the definition of reports and datasets
Overseeing the successful distribution and communication to relevant stakeholders through Analytics Portal
Designing workflows to automate data ingestion, validation and report delivery mechanisms 
Helping define the data sourcing and API strategy, in collaboration with the Data Architecture and Integration team and IT
Supporting the reporting needs of business stakeholders in a timely and professional manner
The success in this role will demonstrate itself through the ability to: 
Understand the business and rationalize the reporting design to directly answer the key business requirements
Identify and develop the appropriate dataset objects (reports, filters, metrics, etc.) to support the development of Business Intelligence solutions
Adhere to the project plan and finding opportunities for shorten the development timeline
Demonstrate a deep technical knowledge across the different stages of the development life cycle of BI platforms
Proactively identify and propose alternatives to improve the stability, performance, and accuracy of the reporting infrastructure


What are we looking for?To fulfill this role successfully, you must possess the following minimum qualifications and experience:
Minimum Education: BA/BS Bachelor's Degree
Minimum Years of Experience: three (3) years working in the field of Analytics
Minimum Years of Experience: two (2) years of experience creating reports, dashboards, and/or summarizing large amounts of data into actionable intelligence to drive business decisions
Additional Requirements (i.e. % of travel time, etc.): 

Experience with leading Business Intelligence tools, preferably MicroStrategy or Tableau 
Demonstrated hands-on experience using SQL and pl/SQL for performing data profiling, formatting, and ad hoc analysis 
Advanced Microsoft and Excel and PowerPoint skills; advanced presentation skills 

It would be advantageous in this position for you to demonstrate the following capabilities and distinctions:
Education: BA/BS Bachelor's Degree in a quantitative discipline such as Computer Science, Information Systems, Mathematics, Statistics or another related field of study
Functional experience in Hospitality
Working experience with Master Data Management tools like Informatica, Talend, Alteryx, Apache Atlas, Collibra, DataStage
End-to-end understanding of the data flow process (from ingestion to consumption layer)
Solid working experience with surrounding and supporting disciplines (data quality, data operations, BI, Data WH, Data Lake)
Experience using R or other statistical analysis and data mining tools 
Working knowledge of Web Services architecture and components like Simple Object Access Protocol (SOAP), Web Services Description Language (WSDL), and/or RESTful web services 
Understanding of data warehousing concepts and relational data models
Familiarity with Agile Project Management
What will it be like to work for Hilton?Hilton is the leading global hospitality company, spanning the lodging sector from luxurious full-service hotels and resorts to extended-stay suites and mid-priced hotels. For nearly a century, Hilton has offered business and leisure travelers the finest in accommodations, service, amenities and value. Hilton is dedicated to continuing its tradition of providing exceptional guest experiences across its global brands.  Our vision to fill the earth with the light and warmth of hospitality unites us as a team to create remarkable hospitality experiences around the world every day.  And, our amazing Team Members are at the heart of it all!
title: Senior Business Intelligence Analyst

details:
Founded in 1866, The Sherwin-Williams Company is a global leader in the manufacture, development, distribution, and sale of paints, coatings and related products to professional, industrial, commercial, and retail customers. The company manufactures products under well-known brands such as Sherwin-Williams®, Valspar®, HGTV HOME® by Sherwin-Williams, Dutch Boy®, Krylon®, Minwax®, Thompson’s® Water Seal®, Cabot® and many more. Sherwin-Williams® branded products are sold exclusively through a chain of more than 4,100 company-operated stores and facilities, while the company’s other brands are sold through leading mass merchandisers, home centers, independent paint dealers, hardware stores, automotive retailers, and industrial distributors. The company supplies a broad range of highly-engineered industrial and OEM coatings for wood and general industrial, coil, packaging, protective and marine, and transportation applications worldwide. Our 60,000 employees are diverse, innovative and passionate. With a variety of rewarding and challenging opportunities, Sherwin-Williams is a great place to find a career that takes you places. The Business Intelligence (BI) Developer’s role is to design and implement BI software and systems.  This includes requirements gathering, analysis, planning, selection, blueprinting, designing, developing, rolling out, and end-user training of BI solutions to the user community.  The Business Intelligence Developer is also responsible for timely data availability and system up-time through support functions and in-depth testing. Essential Functions Strategy & Planning 
Gathers requirements, analyzes, creates design documents, and performs impact analysis.
Assess and cultivate long-term strategic goals for BI development in conjunction with end users, managers, clients, and other stakeholders.
Continuously evaluate industry trends for opportunities to utilize new technologies and data sources for BI improvement and prepare strategies to implement these enhancements in the BI environment.
 Acquisition & Deployment 
Conduct research and make recommendations on BI products, services, and standards in support of procurement and development efforts.
Evaluate and select database/data warehouse components, including hardware, relational database management systems, ETL software, metadata management tools and database design solutions.
Gathers requirements, analyzes, creates design documents, and performs impact analysis.
Provide ongoing support of existing business intelligence implementations.
 Operational Management 
Develop, enhance and maintain the meta data layers, reports, report definitions and dashboards.
Produce guidelines and standards for ETL usage, manageability and maintainability within the organization.
Build database models, dashboards, reports, interfaces for BI packages.
Develops Oracle PL/SQL procedures and other Oracle database development objects.
Assist users with problems and resolves issues independently.
Creates test plans, test cases, test scripts and performs testing of the BI and related environments.
Promote BI benefits to the organization and usage of our tools to relevant business groups.
Provide ongoing support of existing BI implementations.
Plan and organize tasks, reports progress to manager.
 Incidental Functions 
Assist with projects as may be required to contribute to efficiency and effectiveness of the work.
Participate in hiring activities and fulfilling affirmative action obligations and ensuring compliance with the equal employee opportunity policy.
Attend management meetings on behalf of team.
Up to 25% travel required (domestic and international).
Working outside the standard office 7.5 hour work day as required.
 Position Requirements  Formal Education & Certification 
Bachelor degree or foreign equivalent in related field or equivalent experience.  
Oracle certifications are a plus.
 Knowledge & Experience 
5+ years IT experience.
5+ years of business intelligence development and support experience with at least 2 years sourcing and presenting data from Oracle E-Business Suite or another large ERP environment.
2-3 years of experience with an ETL or ELT tool for data extraction transformation and loading.
Well versed in advanced query development and design using SQL.
Well versed with dimensional data modeling and the construction of ETL routines for application modules in one or more of the following realms: financials, supply chain, manufacturing, and point of sales systems.
Experience with one or more of the following: Oracle Business Intelligence Enterprise Edition (OBIEE), Oracle BI Application, Oracle Daily Business Intelligence, Informatica Power Center, Oracle Data Integrator (ODI), Oracle Warehouse Builder or a similar set of tools.
Experience with Oracle BI Applications, a plus.
Experience with MDX, XQuery, XML/A, a plus.
Experience with Star and Snowflake database design modeling using tools including ERWin, DB Artisan, etc., a plus.
Experience with XML development and design including XML Schema, and XSLT are a plus.
Experience with Crystal Reports, Oracle Reports, Hyperion Essbase, MicroStrategy, Microsoft SQL Server Analysis Services (SSAS), Pentaho, Talend, JasperReports, optional.
Experience with web services integration architectures including SOAP and REST, a plus.
Knowledge of scripting languages including Korn/Bourne Shell, Perl, Python, Ruby, a plus.
Experience with quality testing tools, data warehousing & Oracle certifications, a plus.
Experience with Oracle E-Business Suite, a plus.
Experience with Java development is a plus.
 Personal Attributes 
Strong written and oral communications skills.
Proven ability and initiative to learn and research new concepts, ideas, and technologies quickly.
Strong systems/process orientation with demonstrated analytical thinking, organization skills and problem solving skills.
Ability to work in a team-oriented, collaborative environment.
Ability to quickly pick up new tools and technologies. 
Willingness and ability to train and teach others.
Ability to facilitate meetings and follow up with resulting action items.
Ability to prioritize and execute tasks in a high-pressure environment.
Strong presentation and interpersonal skills. 
Ability to work effectively in a multi-cultural environment, and to lead and influence cross-organizationally with and without direct authority.
Ability to effectively move forward on tasks even with ambiguous or changing requirements.

title: Consultant-Network Business Intelligence

details:
Did you know that Gartner positioned eXcell as a Leader in its Magic Quadrant for End User Outsourcing? Come work for the leader today!
 
The Business Intelligence (BI) Analyst identifies business intelligence, reporting, and data analysis needs. They work closely with clients and IT teams to turn data into critical information and knowledge that can be used to make sound business decisions. They provide data that is accurate, congruent, and reliable, and ensure the information is easily available to users for direct consumption or integration with other systems.
 
Overview:

Work with clients (internal or external) to determine business requirements, priorities, define key performance indicators (KPI)
Build an understanding of the business at a level of detail that enables them to identify and address critical issues
Educate and train clients to use the data as an analytical tool, displaying the information in new forms and content for the purpose of analysis and option exploration
Design and document dashboards, alerts, and reports either on a regular recurring basis or as needed
Conduct analyses of functional business processes and functional business requirements, and participate in the development of business cases in the support of process changes and/or IT projects
Provides design support for the development of business intelligence solutions
Works on medium to complex and cross-functional IT and business intelligence solutions
May perform analysis for a wide range of requests using data in different formats and from various platforms 
Researches business problems and creates models that help analyze those problems

Qualifications:

5-7 years of related experience 
Experience with business intelligence – reporting in BI dashboards, 2-3 years
Telemetry and instrumented data and log analysis, 2-3 years’ experience
Proficiency in Microsoft technology stack, 2-3 years
Degree in Computer Science or Engineering background


W2 only, no Corp to Corp. For more information, visit www.excell.com.

details:
HealthTrust (www.healthtrustpg.com) is committed to strengthening provider performance and clinical excellence through an aligned membership model and the delivery of total spend management solutions that leverage our operator experience, scale and innovation. Members include approximately 1,600 acute care facilities and more than 26,000 non-acute care sites.  Job Summary – The BI Analyst II provides leadership and support specific to the development of reports within Supply Chain Financial Operations.  Requiring technical/BI awareness, this analytically-focused position is responsible for the interpretation and understanding of information systems used to serve the business and to drive supply expense savings. This individual will leverage existing reports and analytics to analyze business problems and processes to harness business intelligence knowledge and improve BI solutions across the enterprise. This goal will be achieved by working with cross-functional business teams and utilizing Tableau, Microstrategy, and/or Business Objects. The BI Analyst II is responsible for actively participating in the analysis of multiple aspects of the BI lifecycle from requirements gathering to data analysis, report analysis, and understanding of business processes. The BI Analyst II will ensure a standardized and consistent approach relating to BI report participation and implementation of Data Governance, and Analytics.  Participates in agile execution of the product lifecycle, the development of solution vision and goals and is responsible for ensuring quality of delivered products.  This position requires both strategic and tactical skillsets with expertise in database navigation, intellectual curiosity, and proficiency at problem solving. Duties (included but not limited to):
Participate in analysis of multiple aspects of the BI lifecycle from requirements to data analysis, report analysis, and understanding of business processes.
Assist in analysis of BI Reporting architecture and report creation, analysis of guided analytics, and other BI solutions.
Produce BI solution designs that meet business requirements in a manner consistent with company and industry standards.
Ensure a standardized and consistent approach relating to BI participation and implementation of Data Governance, Business Intelligence (BI) and Analytics.
With direction and supervision act as subject matter specialist to assist development of the appropriate strategies, plans, tools and approaches to ensure successful implementation of BI reports, dashboards and scorecards.
Work to think analytically and critically to take ownership of reporting standardization and automating efforts.
Present data formally and informally, facilitating discussions regarding data outputs.
Participate in multi-disciplinary teams to use data in improving usage and operational workflow.
Utilize internal and external training opportunities to cross train on other Business Intelligence tools and database platforms such as Business Objects, Microstrategy, Tableau Desktop & Server, Qlik Tech products, SQL Server, Teradata, or others. 
Grow professionally to assume greater responsibilities for the activities listed above and demonstrate hands-on technical capability for development projects.
Provide moderate analysis and ad-hoc operational reports as requested by Group, Division, and Corporate leaders.
Identify reporting needs to support usage goals throughout the Facility, Division, and Group levels of HCA.
With direction, provide in depth “what if” analysis of data using available tools
Participate in operational performance reviews on an as-needed basis.
Practice and adhere to the “Code of Conduct” philosophy and “Mission and Value Statement”.
Other duties as assigned by the Manager of Supply Chain Analytics.



Bachelor’s Degree required
Minimum of 3 years of progressively-responsible experience in a technical and/or analytics-based environment required.
Demonstrated SQL experience required, experience with Teradata and SQL Server desired.
Experience in an Agile BI Reporting development environment highly desirable.
Experience in a Supply Chain related field (Demand / Supply/ Inventory / Production / Material / Master / Capacity Planning, Warehousing and/or Optimization) preferred.

title: Business Intelligence Associate

details: Description The BI Data Warehouse Architect is responsible for being a key member of our Business Intelligence team, focusing on data architecture, dimensional modeling, platform architecture, solution breakdown, and evangelism of BI best practices and standards. This role is responsible for the design and architecture of the overall BI solution and associated data structures. Essential Duties and Responsibilities:  Define technical principles, vision, and standards for data within our BI platforms Effectively and objectively research BI technology concepts and tools, making recommendations to relevant stakeholders Develop and evangelize standards used within BI, including Data Warehouse(DW) best practices and design patterns, frameworks and templates, naming conventions and coding standards Develop dimensional modeling best practices, and act as subject matter expert and guide for data models across all areas of the business Ensure the DW design can scale to handle additional data demands and can adapt to new business questions and data sets Understand and make recommendations on the underlying hardware and software platforms that host all layers of BI. Expert-level Azure knowledge is expected. Define and recommend ETL processes and associated timings Serve as a lead on ETL development, unit testing, break/fix support. Lend technical expertise to dimensional modeling activities Support the development and execution of system design reviews and query/code review processes Help with project-level technical estimates and timelines Help to establish and improve data governance methodologies Help facilitate the training of DW and BI users Performs other duties as assigned by Management  Supervisory Responsibilities:  None. Qualifications:  To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential duty satisfactorily.  The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skills and abilities required.  Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions of this job. Educations and/or Experience: Required  Requires B.S. degree in computer science and a minimum of 5 years of relevant experience in the BI space Proven experience using the Azure BI stack to deliver enterprise-level BI projects Proven Azure-based DW analysis, design, and data-modeling experience Ability to make cost-effective technical decisions and recommendations using Azure technology Expert-level SQL Server 2014+ experience Expert-level Azure Analysis Services (Tabular) experience Years of experience working with SSIS, SSRS, SSDT for Visual Studio and related tools Expert-level PowerBI, DAX, and M knowledge Extensive experience with developing, unit testing, break/fix support of ETL Experience with data warehouse/decision support modeling Experienced at leading dimensional modeling activities and defining conformed dimensions that will work across multiple data marts Experience supporting and troubleshooting data flow into front-end BI dashboards Years of experience using Agile development methodologies to deliver BI projects Experience using PowerShell to manage Azure resources.  Preferred:  “MCSE: Cloud Platform and Infrastructure” and/or “MCSD: Azure Solutions Architect” certifications are a huge plus Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in computer engineering or related field Experience implementing MS Master Data Management Experience serving as a scrum-master for a development team Experience providing data support for predictive analytics projects Experience developing training materials and training users in the use of modern analysis tools such as PowerBI. Experience with multi-vendor hybrid cloud data warehousing Experience using AWS data structures for hybrid reporting (Redshift, DynamoDB, etc.)  Language Skills:  Ability to read and interpret documents of advanced technical complexity.  Ability to create reports and apply technical research to real world problems. Ability to speak and present effectively one-on-one as well as in small and large groups of professionals including customers, clients and collaborators, both inside and outside the organization. Mathematical Skills:  Ability to apply advanced mathematics principles while performing essential job duties. Reasoning Ability:  Advanced reasoning skills required.  Must have the ability to solve complex problems and weigh possible solutions to determine rank options to deliver optimal outcomes.  Ability to assess problems involving several variables in changing situations. Physical Demands:  The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job.  Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions. While performing the duties of this Job, the employee is regularly required to sit and talk or hear.  The employee is occasionally required to stand and walk.  The employee must occasionally lift and/or move up to 25 pounds.  Work Environment:   The work environment characteristics described here are representative of those an employee encounters while performing the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions. Background must demonstrate the ability to operate effectively within a complex, dynamic environment. title: 2791 - Microsoft Business Intelligence Developer - Nashua, NH- Tara Blvd.

details:
HealthTrust (www.healthtrustpg.com) is committed to strengthening provider performance and clinical excellence through an aligned membership model and the delivery of total spend management solutions that leverage our operator experience, scale and innovation. Members include approximately 1,600 acute care facilities and more than 26,000 non-acute care sites.  Job Summary – The BI Analyst II provides leadership and support specific to the development of reports within Supply Chain Financial Operations.  Requiring technical/BI awareness, this analytically-focused position is responsible for the interpretation and understanding of information systems used to serve the business and to drive supply expense savings. This individual will leverage existing reports and analytics to analyze business problems and processes to harness business intelligence knowledge and improve BI solutions across the enterprise. This goal will be achieved by working with cross-functional business teams and utilizing Tableau, Microstrategy, and/or Business Objects. The BI Analyst II is responsible for actively participating in the analysis of multiple aspects of the BI lifecycle from requirements gathering to data analysis, report analysis, and understanding of business processes. The BI Analyst II will ensure a standardized and consistent approach relating to BI report participation and implementation of Data Governance, and Analytics.  Participates in agile execution of the product lifecycle, the development of solution vision and goals and is responsible for ensuring quality of delivered products.  This position requires both strategic and tactical skillsets with expertise in database navigation, intellectual curiosity, and proficiency at problem solving. Duties (included but not limited to):
Participate in analysis of multiple aspects of the BI lifecycle from requirements to data analysis, report analysis, and understanding of business processes.
Assist in analysis of BI Reporting architecture and report creation, analysis of guided analytics, and other BI solutions.
Produce BI solution designs that meet business requirements in a manner consistent with company and industry standards.
Ensure a standardized and consistent approach relating to BI participation and implementation of Data Governance, Business Intelligence (BI) and Analytics.
With direction and supervision act as subject matter specialist to assist development of the appropriate strategies, plans, tools and approaches to ensure successful implementation of BI reports, dashboards and scorecards.
Work to think analytically and critically to take ownership of reporting standardization and automating efforts.
Present data formally and informally, facilitating discussions regarding data outputs.
Participate in multi-disciplinary teams to use data in improving usage and operational workflow.
Utilize internal and external training opportunities to cross train on other Business Intelligence tools and database platforms such as Business Objects, Microstrategy, Tableau Desktop & Server, Qlik Tech products, SQL Server, Teradata, or others. 
Grow professionally to assume greater responsibilities for the activities listed above and demonstrate hands-on technical capability for development projects.
Provide moderate analysis and ad-hoc operational reports as requested by Group, Division, and Corporate leaders.
Identify reporting needs to support usage goals throughout the Facility, Division, and Group levels of HCA.
With direction, provide in depth “what if” analysis of data using available tools
Participate in operational performance reviews on an as-needed basis.
Practice and adhere to the “Code of Conduct” philosophy and “Mission and Value Statement”.
Other duties as assigned by the Manager of Supply Chain Analytics.




Bachelor’s Degree required
Minimum of 3 years of progressively-responsible experience in a technical and/or analytics-based environment required.
Demonstrated SQL experience required, experience with Teradata and SQL Server desired.
Experience in an Agile BI Reporting development environment highly desirable.
Experience in a Supply Chain related field (Demand / Supply/ Inventory / Production / Material / Master / Capacity Planning, Warehousing and/or Optimization) preferred.

title: REMOTE Power BI Report Developer (Dynamics NAV)

details:
The BI Reporting Analyst will serve as the front-line resource in managing reporting requests and requirements for the DentaQuest enterprise.  The BI Operations Team will create and maintain the processes for deploying new reporting solutions and functionality into production, enhancing current production solutions and providing consistent quality service levels to internal and external customers.

The Reporting Analyst will interact regularly with internal or external business clients to capture and understand reporting and report data service requests, will help define and clarify requirements, define and propose appropriate solutions, and provide guidance for development of the reporting solution to the development team. They will perform quality review of developed solutions and ensure proper user acceptance.  They will promote and educate the organization on the benefits of self-service products and support projects and products that enable overall BI goals.
JOB DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:                                      

Maintain the production Business Intelligence products and solutions, including resolving production issues and responding quickly to priority problems
Perform intake review and assist in prioritization of reporting requests
Analyze reporting service requests and define technical specifications for efficient development
Work with other BI team members in maintaining reporting standards and protocols
Identify opportunities for self-service and educate the business on self-service capabilities
Analyze data and data requirements regarding reporting solutions, ensure data quality and match-back to core systems transaction results.
Maintain documentation of reporting solutions, data mapping, data dictionary, and reporting standards
Perform quality review of new and existing reporting solutions.  Coordinate end user review and acceptance of the developed solutions
Support IT goals and objectives by working closely with management team to deliver value to the business
Other duties as assigned.

Required Skills

Strong knowledge of relational database applications and data query protocols (MS access, SQL Server, Structured Query Language, SQL Reporting Services)
Working experience with end user Report design, development and implementation with a strong focus on Microsoft and Cognos tools
Demonstrated ability to drive to deadlines, balancing multiple priorities, and ensuring quality standards
Excellent analytical, problem-solving, and innovative thinking skills
Excellent organization and prioritization skills with strong ability to multi-task and shift focus as necessary to meet deadlines.
Excellent interpersonal listening, verbal, and written communication skills. Ability to communicate technical details to technical and non-technical resources. Ability to interact effectively with people at all levels and functions across the business.



 JOB REQUIREMENTS:

BS degree in Business, Computer Science, Engineering, Information Systems or related field (or equivalent experience)
3+ years in Information Technology, 1+ years developing reporting or technical solutions (warehouses, SSIS, stored procedures, marts, reports)
Experience with SSIS, OLTP/OLAP, SSAS, Reporting Services (SSRS), Report Builder, Stored Procedures, CDC, Cognos, and C#
Expertise and hands-on experience with complex SQL queries and object oriented programming techniques
Experience in roles where multi-level staff or client interaction is required
Insurance industry experience preferred.

title: Business Intelligence Developer

details:
If you are a BI or Data Analyst living in the northwest metro Atlanta area, and have been looking for an opportunity to work closer to home, then your opportunity has finally arrived. Our Cherokee count based client is looking for a Data Analyst to handle process standardization and automation. There is a chance hear to learn robotic process automation. You need to have solid SQL skills and experience as well has being able to speak to your experience making business process improvements. Any experience with JDE gets you to the front of the line.
Job Summary:
The Data Analyst is responsible for analyzing large amounts of raw information to find patterns that will help improve business processes and data intelligence of the company. We will rely on the Data Analyst to build data products to extract valuable business insights.
In this role, you should be highly analytical with a knack for analysis, math and statistics. Critical thinking and problem-solving skills are essential for interpreting data. We also want to see a passion for process standardization and automation. 
Your goal will be to help our company utilize data to make better decisions.
Job Responsibilities:
•             Work with stakeholders throughout the organization to identify opportunities for leveraging company data to drive business decisions.
•             Mine and analyze data from company databases to drive process and reporting optimization and standardization.
•             Assess the effectiveness and accuracy of new data sources and data gathering techniques.
•             Develop and maintain reporting dashboards and scorecards.
•             Use predictive modeling to increase and optimize customer experiences.
•             Coordinate with different functional teams to implement models and monitor outcomes.
•             Develop processes and tools to monitor and analyze business services model performance and data accuracy.
Successful incumbents will have:
•             Proven experience as a BI Analyst or Data Analyst
•             Experience in data mining
•             Experience using business intelligence and automation tools (e.g. Tableau, Celonis, UiPath RPA)  
•             Analytical mind and business acumen
•             Strong math skills (e.g. statistics, algebra)
•             Problem-solving aptitude
•             Excellent communication and presentation skills
•             BS/BA in Computer Science, Engineering or relevant field; graduate degree in Data Science or other quantitative field is preferred
•             Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, technology driven, service environment leveraging innovation and collaboration.
•             Energetic, can-do attitude, forward-thinking leader and strong ability to multi-task.
•             Experience with process improvement and/or change management.
•             Strong commercial acumen and customer service focus
•             Think analytically, focus on the big picture, and able to drill into the detail and understand the impact. Understand how the business operates and the upstream and downstream activities that impact and are impacted by Business Services.
Position Scope/Contribution:
The successful candidate will be a driver of transformation and change. This includes managing these initiatives to ensure successful implementation. The role will provide oversight to department managers who manage day to day operations to support the business strategies ensuring continuous improvement and exceptional client service.

Description
As a Senior Business Intelligence Analyst, you will be charged with providing analytics reporting and data-driven strategic insights, trends and perspectives. The ideal candidate will develop and maintain relevant reporting and perform critical data analysis necessary to monitor and improve revenue-related business goals for Bankrate.com, a division of Red Ventures. This role requires a proactive personality, extremely analytical mindset, attention to detail, and excellent time management and communication skills.  This role will report to the Director of Business Intelligence and will be based in the Bankrate.com New York City Office.
Responsibilities

Own the data, analytics, and reporting to empower business verticals and build data innovations.
Collaborate closely with all areas of the business (Product, SEO, Performance Marketing, Business Development, Social, Email, Sales, Marketing, Finance, Display/AdOps) to provide analysis, reporting and tool-building capabilities that inform our key stakeholders
Utilize internal/external data sources to develop and maintain dynamic and scalable dashboards to track key performance metrics for the Bankrate Vertical businesses as well as specific sources of traffic, channels, or products.
Investigate and analyze traffic trends using Google Analytics and data from other proprietary sources.
Develop ROI business cases to support new and existing product development.
Plan and execute methodical A/B tests to improve user experience and optimize revenue.
Ensure data integrity across all performance-based metrics, tracking and reporting.
Interpret and communicate information in a manner that can be comprehended by non-analytical audience. 

Required Skills

Undergraduate or Master’s degree in a quantitative field (e.g. engineering, business, economics, finance, statistics, and analytics).
Strong analytical background with a proven track record demonstrating an aptitude to compile data in comprehensive reports, analyze trends and make fact-based recommendations
Strong experience with data extraction, manipulation and blending across different data sources (Google Analytics, DoubleClick for Publishers, SQL Server, Snowflake, AWS, Salesforce, flat files, etc). Experience with ETL tools a plus.
Strong experience with Google Analytics or other web analytics tools. Google Tag Manager (GTM) experience a plus.
Strong experience with using BI tools to build dynamic/scalable dashboards. Looker experience a plus.
Proficient at writing SQL queries against complex databases for the purpose of data extraction.
Experience with A/B, multivariate testing tools such as Optimizely.
Knowledge of the Internet landscape, including a comprehension of display advertising, lead-oriented/search-oriented (cost per click, cost per lead, cost per call) business models.
Ability to translate business questions into problems solvable using analytics tools, and enjoy converting the results of your analyses into visual stories tailored to the needs of the audience.
Strong written and verbal communication skills and have experience working on and communicating with fast-paced, dynamic teams.
Excellent Excel and PowerPoint Skills
Team-oriented, self-motivated, success-driven, roll-up-your-sleeves attitude

About Red Ventures:
Red Ventures is a leading digital consumer choice platform based in Charlotte, North Carolina. Through deeply integrated brand partnerships and consumer-facing assets, Red Ventures connects online customers with products and services across high-growth industries including home services, financial services, and healthcare. Founded in 2000, Red Ventures has more than 2,700 employees in offices across the Carolinas, Seattle, Washington, London, UK, and Sao Paulo, Brazil.  
About Bankrate:
Bankrate is a leading publisher, aggregator, and distributor of personal finance content. Bankrate provides consumers with fully researched, comprehensive, independent and objective personal finance editorial content across multiple vertical categories including mortgages, deposits, insurance, credit cards, and other categories, such as retirement, automobile loans, and taxes. For over two decades Bankrate.com has been a leading personal finance destination. Bankrate aggregates rate information from over 4,800 institutions on more than 300 financial products. With coverage for over 600 local markets, Bankrate generates rate tables in all 50 US states. Bankrate develops and provides web services to more than 100 cobranded websites with online partners such as Bloomberg, Comcast, Yahoo! And CNBC.

title: BI and Data Analytics Developer

details:
Equity Staffing Group is hiring a BI Developer to work on an exciting new project building out a Google Big Query Data warehouse. Our client is implementing a data integration and analytics platform to support clinical and translational healthcare research to promote operational excellence within partner hospitals, and to drive innovation and discovery in the field of personalized medicine. This BI Developer position is responsible to design and develop reports, dashboards, data extracts, and visualizations from across a variety of healthcare and biomedical research data domains. Primary reporting platforms are custom reports, including Excel, and Tableau, but we anticipate the use of other technologies for visualization and analysis, such as R or Python. In addition, this person will participate in the design of the dimensional models behind these outputs. The BI developer will be a key member of our strong, highly collaborative team, working with customers, analysts, and other technical personnel throughout all phases of the software development lifecycle.

Examples of Work Performed:

•Develops efficient SQL queries and designs algorithms to extract data from cloud-based data warehouses like Google BigQuery, and/or relational databases like SQL Server. (40%)
•Formats result datasets to follow standard data input process for reporting platforms. (10%) 
•Designs and develops data visualization products using Tableau Desktop, R, SAS, and other tools. (10%) 
•Validates and tests output result accuracy; performs code review, data product user-acceptance testing, and other related testing. (10%) 
•Profiles and understands enterprise data warehouses in order to answer research-based questions. (10%) 
•Creates and/or maintains documentation for query design, report definition, data mappings, code review logs, validation results, etc. (5%) 
•Manages incidents and resolves problems with thorough analysis, troubleshooting and validation techniques. (5%) 
•Helps drive technical strategies in support of the overall program. (5%)
•Works closely with others on the technical team to collaborate, design, problem solve and troubleshoot. (5%) 

Minimum Qualifications:
•Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Computer Information Systems, Mathematics, Statistics, Biosciences or related field. 
•2+ years of industry experience working as a BI developer, data analyst or report writer. 
•2+ years of experience developing SQL queries to extract data from relational databases, such as SQL Server, Oracle, etc. 

Preferred Qualifications:
•Master’s degree or related experience 
•Experience with automated testing 
•Experience with a variety of healthcare and biomedical research data domains, like EMR data in EPIC Caboodle, OMOP, and a variety of other healthcare data models, 
•Experience with a variety of BI tools, e.g., Business Objects, Tableau
•Experience with analytical tools and methods, e.g., R, SAS, Python. 
•Experience with data warehouses hosted on cloud platforms, such as Google Cloud, AWS, etc. 
•Experience with Genomics data.

Knowledge, Skills and Abilities:

•Ability to excel in an integrated environment, working closely with various IT, business, and user teams to accomplish objectives. 
•In-depth knowledge of relational databases, OLAP query tools, data mining, data structure, and data manipulation techniques. 
•Advanced level of knowledge of SQL and Transact-SQL.
•Demonstrated ability to design, develop and validate BI outputs using Tableau or a similar tool, with thorough understanding of metadata layers and user interactivity.
•Demonstrated ability to troubleshoot and resolve bugs relating to data accuracy, usability, and performance issues. 
•Direct experience with large data warehouses. 
•Ability to analyze clinical and business source systems on a variety of platforms.

details:
Amazon is looking for a Sr. Business Intelligence Engineer for Amazon Devices. This person will design and develop data visualizations that help us extract key insights from our data, which might otherwise go unnoticed. This role is central to the continued growth of the Amazon Devices division as it continues its fast-paced growth and expansion from the first Kindle e-Reader to a broad portfolio of Fire Tablets, Fire TVs, and most recently, Echo.   The mission of our Worldwide Planning organization is to deliver the most accurate forecasts, inventory targets, and allocation plans to ensure every customer is able to purchase the product they want, when and where they want it. In order to achieve this, our team develops and uses optimization tools, advanced statistical models, machine learning algorithms and big data solutions, to provide the Device organization with a forecast and operational plan.  As our organization's Sr. Business Intelligence Engineer you would be responsible for creating compelling, clear, and powerful visualizations of our data. We want our data to tell a clear story, highlight insights we hadn't previously seen, and do it all faster than we've been able to previously. We want someone to work on this full-time, lead our efforts, and improve everyone's work by example and by improving the tools we use to do so. Technology hands-on expert in specialty area.

Meet regularly with project technical leads and solution architects to review designs, recommend solutions and participate in code reviews for applicable systems for all activities related to upgrades, patches, releases, production schedules, disaster recovery plans.

Write technical specifications.

Studio 2010+, Team Foundation Server 2012+, MS Build and/or Eclipse,
Subversion, Ant.

details:
HCA, a Fortune 100 company with more than 200,000 employees, is one of the nation's leading providers of healthcare services, operating over 170 locally managed hospitals and over 100 freestanding surgery centers in 20 states and the United Kingdom. With its founding in 1968, HCA created a new model for hospital care in the United States, using combined resources to strengthen hospitals, deliver patient-focused care and improve the practice of medicine. HCA is a learning healthcare system that uses more than 27 million annual patient encounters to advance science, improve patient care and save lives. HCA has been named one of the world's most ethical companies for eight years in a row. At HCA, we are driven by a single goal: the care and improvement of human life.JOB SUMMARY    The Analytics & Pricing Services (APS) Consulting Contract Analyst is responsible for the What-if modeling of the more advanced managed care contracts and performance of advanced ad hoc analyses as assigned by departmental director, and manager.GENERAL RESPONSIBILITIES1.  Assist in the design, development and implementation of advanced adhoc reports.  Assist in identifying and documenting reporting requirements.  
 Based on data sources identified, extract and manipulate data from databases.
 Assist with performing acceptance and QA testing as applicable.
 Review reports of Senior Financial Analyst.
  2.  Model more advanced managed care contracts through the Alliance for Decision Support system (ADS).  Review models and audit work of Senior Analyst and Analyst.
 Reconcile populations for what-if negotiations with payors.
 Understand and analyze CDM price increases to determine the effect on contract modeling, negotiations, and net revenue projections.
 Organize and analyzes results data providing summary of findings Consulting FA, and Manager.  Provide information related to how changes related to both CDM and rates could impact net revenue.
 Set or assist with establishing rates for contracts.
  3.  Completes retrospective review of contracts to analyze negotiated rate of reimbursement compared to actual net revenue results with variance explanation. 4.  Completes testing of contract models by service line and keeps documentation of accuracy in permanent work paper files.  5.  Uses data mining tools to assist customers effectively with data requests. 6.  Serve as liaison with the SSC/CPCM modelers, communicating contract information related to renegotiated and new contracts. 7.  Provide training/education.  Work with Analyst to develop documentation. 8.  Maintain Managed Care MOR on a monthly basis. 9.  Participate in departmental training and professional development opportunities when available. 10.  Adds value to APS by producing accurate results, working efficiently, and continuing to grow in the position.

EXPERIENCE7 - 10 years of experience EDUCATION College Graduate Required - UndergradSPECIAL QUALIFICATIONS  Minimum 3-7 years HCA experience preferred.  Proven ability to manage project work.  Required understanding of gross/net revenue, managed care payors, data availability, and HCA financial systems.  Working knowledge of managed care contracting and modeling required.Required experience with QlikView/QlikSense, MS Access and Excel, Business Objects, and SQL.  Also, experience with Datamarts, Essbase, Microstrategy, Oracle, Relational Database’s, SAP Business Warehouse, and Tableau would be preferred.#LI-PT1INDKD

To promote the mission of PATH to help individuals achieve a more independent and fulfilling life by being an effective and engaged team member in a residential program for adults with intellectual disabilities.
Specific Duties 

Support individuals by providing assistance and training in all areas of daily living, including, but not limited to the following:

hygiene, grooming
care of clothing, laundry
cooking, nutrition, dietary needs, meal preparation, menu development, grocery shopping
household maintenance, cleaning
budgeting, banking, comparative buying, financial documentation in accordance with PATH’s  Fiscal Policies and Procedures
leisure activities, recreation
appropriate social skills
utilizing various modes of transportation for community integrated activities
awareness and use of community resources


Participate in the Individual Support Planning Process by:

attending and contributing to annual and ancillary meetings, as scheduled
assuring individual’s rights are respected, implemented and consistent with DPW/ODP regulations 
implementing program outcomes
documenting outcome progress
completing monthly reports
supporting individuals’ independence as defined in Independence Time Summaries and program plans


Assist individuals in maintaining good health by:

assuming knowledge of  individual’s medical history and current health issues
assuming knowledge of an individual’s physician and ancillary health professionals
accompanying an individual to medical appointments or emergency service, as necessary
communicating with supervisory and healthcare staff about the health needs of an individual
adhering to PATH’s Medication Administration Policy


Assure individuals’ safety in the home by:

teaching safety precautions in the home

 conducting monthly fire drills, which includes checking the fire extinguishers and smoke alarms daily
 submitting repair requests for maintenance items
 notifying supervisory staff of emergency/ health & safety concerns


Teaching safety precautions in the community by:

 assisting in mobility training and awareness of traffic signs
 assuring “stranger” awareness
 learning emergency contacts
 assisting individuals in maintaining and carrying personal identification




Address various individual needs by:

communicating with co-workers and the appropriate supervisor
reviewing communication logs during each shift worked
documenting daily in all communication logs
communicating with families, guardians, advocates, neighbors and other program staff in a professional manner
notifying the on-call supervisor of emergencies via team cell phone


Support and assist individuals in maintaining their home by involving the individual in:

shopping for food and other household purchases
preparing meals, as appropriate
managing weekly household expenses
weekly household cleaning
self medication as needed


Acquire a minimum 24 hours of training annually, within required time frames, including, but not limited to:

Medication Administration and annual reviews
Fire Safety
CPR
First Aid
Infection Control
Crisis Intervention
Diabetes certification, as needed 




High School Diploma or GED required.  Experience preferred in working with the ID population or co-occurring ID/MH population.  Must be at least 18 years of age and be physically able to perform the functions of the job.  Valid driver’s license preferred.

What can YOU do with the right information? At Optum360, the possibilities and the impact are limitless. You'll be empowered to ask more questions, develop better solutions, and help make the health care system greater than ever.
Join the Optum360 Business Intelligence team and you’ll serve as a revenue cycle industry expert primarily responsible for designing and delivering best-practice reporting and analytics solutions for our enterprise partners. This Business Intelligence Analytics Associate role will require individuals to combine their leadership capabilities, industry experience, and understanding of revenue cycle performance solutions to help generate world-class results.
This position gives you the opportunity to see your ideas come to life and your achievements recognized. You won't find tougher challenges. And you won't find smarter people working together to solve them.  Join us and start doing your life's best work.(sm)

You'll enjoy the flexibility to telecommute* from anywhere within the U.S. as you take on some tough challenges.
Typical projects include, but are not limited to:

Design, implementation, and support of revenue cycle dashboards and reports 

Conducting revenue cycle assessment and benchmarking efforts 

Sourcing data from multiple systems into an enterprise data warehouse

Alignment and implementation of partner processes and Optum360 technology

Patient access (scheduling, pre-registration, insurance verification, financial counseling) 

Registration/Admission (ED, inpatient, outpatient, ambulatory)

Decision support and analytics 

Productivity and quality management



Identify partner accomplishments and barriers in achieving operational excellence

Collaborate with partners and internal departments to design and implement dashboards and reports 

Understand and represent Optum360 Business Intelligence and services and how they will improve partner operations 

Collaborate with partner revenue cycle teams to facilitate resolution of process issues and implement world-class solutions 

Provide informed feedback to Optum360 and partner executives including assessments of processes, standards, suggestions and improvements 

Assist in the sales process as requested 

Develop work plans, project tasks, and manage projects in accordance with budget standards

Required Qualifications:

Bachelor's Degree 

2+ years of experience in health care revenue cycle 

Expert in MS Office Suite productivity tools (Word, Excel, Visio, Outlook, and PowerPoint) 

Experience in business intelligence visualization tools (Mede/Analytics, Tableau, Qlik, Health Catalyst, Alteryx, etc.) 

Experience and comfort working at all levels of a health care organization 

Ability to probe, analyze, synthesize, and articulate complex technical subject matter so it can be easily understood 

A high degree of self-motivation, versatility, and flexibility 

Working knowledge of hospital-based IT systems 

Excellent interpersonal, written, and oral communication skills 

Excellent presentation skills 

Ability to lead, direct and motivate others 

Ability to build effective teams in order to accomplish goals 

Ability to maintain the highest level of confidentiality 

Ability to travel up to 75%

Preferred Qualifications:
Bachelor's degree in Business, Finance and Accounting or related degree field 

Experience in health care host systems (Envision, Soarian, McKesson, etc.).
Careers with Optum. Here's the idea. We built an entire organization around one giant objective; make health care work better for everyone. So when it comes to how we use the world's large accumulation of health-related information, or guide health and lifestyle choices or manage pharmacy benefits for millions, our first goal is to leap beyond the status quo and uncover new ways to serve. Optum, part of the UnitedHealth Group family of businesses, brings together some of the greatest minds and most advanced ideas on where health care has to go in order to reach its fullest potential. For you, that means working on high performance teams against sophisticated challenges that matter. With global reach, outcome-focused methodologies and deep industry expertise, IBM GBS empowers clients to digitally reinvent their business and get the competitive edge in the cognitive era in over 170 countries. Bottom line? We outthink ordinary. Discover what you can do at IBM. The IBM Client Innovation Center in Baton Rouge has an immediate opportunity for an experienced forward thinking SAP BI/HANA Consultant with a passion for growth and innovation. Join our team and utilize leading-edge technology to configure, develop, deliver and support applications for our clients in areas such as Mobile, Big Data, Cloud Computing or Smarter Commerce. Our clients are some of the world’s leading companies and you will be part of challenging projects to build and support technical solutions for their needs.  he SAP BI/HANA Consultant has the primary responsibility for the rollout of technical and functional aspects of the SAP BI / HANA solution. The SAP BI / HANA Consultant will lead the integrated planning, design, implementation and support of SAP BI / HANA based solutions including SAP LT Replication Server, SAP ECC, SAP Data Services, SAP Business Warehouse (BW), Enterprise (Native) HANA and SAP BI/Business Objects in large and complex environments.This position requires excellent verbal and written communication skills, ability to interact with both business and technical stakeholders of client companies and a proven track record designing and implementing SAP (Native) HANA Solutions, traditional SAP Business Warehouse (BW) and BW on HANA solutions. The candidate must be a team player, proactive, an effective communicator with ability to work independently and manage other development resources. With access to resources that only a global leader can provide, as a consultant you will learn valuable skills, gain access to a vast and diverse network of talented professionals, and enjoy unparalleled career, training, and educational opportunities. However, some travel is expected and all candidates must be willing and able to travel to meet our client needs. Travel expectations are approximately 50%. No remote opportunities exist.
